initial data is realized as an honest `L¬≤(ūĚēč¬≤)`-valued SQG solution
satisfying the evolution axioms.

The structured (Duhamel-level) `SqgEvolutionAxioms_strong` promotion
via ¬ß10.94 requires `HasDerivAt` on all of `‚ĄĚ`, one notch stronger
than the `HasDerivWithinAt ... (Ici 0)` delivered by ¬ß10.116; that
upgrade is not pursued here. `SqgEvolutionAxioms` alone is the
structure consumed by `SqgSolution`, which is what the README open
item asked to produce. -/

/-- **¬ß10.117.A ‚ÄĒ ŠłĘ‚Āį seminorm of `galerkinToLp` as a finite sum.**
Standalone form of the `hExp` step inside
`galerkinToLp_hsSeminormSq_zero_const`. For any Galerkin state `c` on
a support `S` with `0 ‚ąČ S`, the ŠłĘ‚Āį seminorm squared of the lifted
trigonometric polynomial coincides with the finite L¬≤ coordinate sum
`‚ąĎ_{m ‚ąą S} ‚ÄĖc m‚ÄĖ¬≤`. Independent of any ODE dynamics. -/
theorem hsSeminormSq_zero_galerkinToLp
    {S : Finset (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)} [DecidableEq (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)]
    (h0 : (0 : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚ąČ S) (c : ‚Ü•S ‚Üí ‚Ąā) :
    hsSeminormSq 0 (galerkinToLp S c) = ‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•S, ‚ÄĖc m‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := by
  unfold hsSeminormSq
  have hZeroOff : ‚ąÄ n ‚ąČ S,
      (fracDerivSymbol 0 n) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (galerkinToLp S c) n‚ÄĖ ^ 2 = 0 := by
    intros n hn
    rw [mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp, galerkinExtend_apply_of_not_mem _ _ hn,
        norm_zero]; ring
  rw [tsum_eq_sum (s := S) (fun n hn => hZeroOff n hn)]
  rw [show ((Finset.univ : Finset ‚Ü•S)) = S.attach from Finset.univ_eq_attach S]
  rw [‚Üź Finset.sum_attach S (fun n =>
      (fracDerivSymbol 0 n) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (galerkinToLp S c) n‚ÄĖ ^ 2)]
  apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
  intros m _
  rw [mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp, galerkinExtend_apply_of_mem _ _ m.property]
  have hm_ne : m.val ‚Č† 0 := fun hv => h0 (hv ‚Ėł m.property)
  rw [fracDerivSymbol_of_ne_zero 0 hm_ne, Real.rpow_zero]; ring

/-- **¬ß10.117.B ‚ÄĒ `SqgEvolutionAxioms` from pure ‚Ąď¬≤ conservation.**
Parallel to ¬ß10.98's `SqgEvolutionAxioms.of_galerkin_dynamics`, but
consumes only the ‚Ąď¬≤-sum invariant (no `HasDerivAt`, no `hRealC`),
matching the output shape of ¬ß10.116's time-global capstone. The
velocity witness is identical to ¬ß10.98. -/
theorem SqgEvolutionAxioms.of_galerkin_realSym_Ici
    {S : Finset (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)} [DecidableEq (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)]
    (h0 : (0 : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚ąČ S)
    (őĪ : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (‚Ü•S ‚Üí ‚Ąā))
    (hL2 : ‚ąÄ t, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
      (‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•S, ‚ÄĖőĪ t m‚ÄĖ ^ 2) = ‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•S, ‚ÄĖőĪ 0 m‚ÄĖ ^ 2) :
    SqgEvolutionAxioms (fun ŌĄ => galerkinToLp S (őĪ ŌĄ)) where
  l2Conservation := fun t ht => by
    rw [hsSeminormSq_zero_galerkinToLp h0, hsSeminormSq_zero_galerkinToLp h0, hL2 t ht]
  meanConservation := fun _ _ => by
    rw [mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp, mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp,
        galerkinExtend_apply_of_not_mem _ _ h0,
        galerkinExtend_apply_of_not_mem _ _ h0]
  velocityIsRieszTransform := fun j =>
    ‚ü®fun ŌĄ => shellVelocity S (galerkinExtend S (őĪ ŌĄ)) j,
      fun ŌĄ => isSqgVelocityComponent_shellMode S (galerkinExtend S (őĪ ŌĄ)) j‚ü©

/-- **¬ß10.117.C ‚ÄĒ Galerkin ‚Üí full-SQG `SqgSolution` existence.**
For any symmetric Fourier support `S ‚äÜ ‚Ą§¬≤` with `0 ‚ąČ S`, any radius
`R > 0`, and any real-symmetric `c‚āÄ : ‚Ü•S ‚Üí ‚Ąā` with `‚ąĎ ‚ÄĖc‚āÄ m‚ÄĖ¬≤ ‚Č§ (R/2)¬≤`,
there exists an `SqgSolution` whose time-zero slice is
`galerkinToLp S c‚āÄ`. The underlying trajectory is
`t ‚Ü¶ galerkinToLp S (őĪ t)`, where `őĪ` is the ¬ß10.116 time-global
Galerkin capstone. Discharges the README "Galerkin ‚Üí full-SQG limit"
open item. -/
theorem exists_sqgSolution_of_galerkin_realSym
    (S : Finset (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)) [DecidableEq (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)]
    (h0 : (0 : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚ąČ S)
    (hS : IsSymmetricSupport S)
    {R : ‚ĄĚ} (hR : 0 < R)
    (c‚āÄ : ‚Ü•S ‚Üí ‚Ąā)
    (hc‚āÄ_l2 : (‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•S, ‚ÄĖc‚āÄ m‚ÄĖ ^ 2) ‚Č§ (R / 2) ^ 2)
    (hRealC‚āÄ : ‚ąÄ n ‚ąą S,
      galerkinExtend S c‚āÄ (-n) = star (galerkinExtend S c‚āÄ n)) :
    ‚ąÉ őł : SqgSolution, őł.őł 0 = galerkinToLp S c‚āÄ := by
  obtain ‚ü®őĪ, hőĪ0, _hderiv, hL2_const, _hRealSym, _hpinorm‚ü© :=
    galerkin_time_global_unconditional_realSym S hS hR c‚āÄ hc‚āÄ_l2 hRealC‚āÄ
  refine ‚ü®{
    őł := fun ŌĄ => galerkinToLp S (őĪ ŌĄ)
    smoothInitialData := ?_
    solvesSqgEvolution := ?_ }, ?_‚ü©
  ¬∑ refine ‚ü®3, by norm_num, ?_‚ü©
    apply hsSeminormSq_summable_of_finite_support 3 (galerkinToLp S (őĪ 0)) S
    intros n hn
    rw [mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp, galerkinExtend_apply_of_not_mem _ _ hn]
  ¬∑ apply SqgEvolutionAxioms.of_galerkin_realSym_Ici h0
    intros t ht
    rw [hőĪ0]
    exact hL2_const t ht
  ¬∑ exact congrArg (galerkinToLp S) hőĪ0

/-! ### ¬ß10.118 `sqgBox n` ‚ÄĒ nested symmetric Fourier boxes on `‚Ą§¬≤`

Canonical exhausting sequence of finite, symmetric, zero-excluding
supports used to truncate arbitrary `L¬≤(ūĚēč¬≤)` Fourier data onto the
¬ß10.116 / ¬ß10.117 Galerkin class. `sqgBox n` is the integer `‚Ąď‚ąě`-ball
of radius `n + 1` minus the origin; the `+ 1` guarantees every mode
eventually enters the sequence.

Properties:
* `zero_not_mem_sqgBox` ‚ÄĒ `0 ‚ąČ sqgBox n`.
* `sqgBox_symmetric` ‚ÄĒ `IsSymmetricSupport (sqgBox n)`.
* `sqgBox_mono` ‚ÄĒ `sqgBox n ‚äÜ sqgBox (n + 1)`.
* `mem_sqgBox_of_linftyNorm_le` ‚ÄĒ membership criterion from the
  per-coordinate bound.
* `exists_mem_sqgBox` ‚ÄĒ exhaustion: every nonzero `m` eventually
  enters `sqgBox n`.
-/

open Finset in
/-- **Canonical nested symmetric Fourier box on `‚Ą§¬≤`.** The integer
`‚Ąď‚ąě`-ball of radius `n + 1` minus the origin, realized as a
`Finset (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)`. Inherits: symmetry under negation, zero-exclusion,
monotonicity in `n`, and eventual exhaustion of `‚Ą§¬≤ ‚ąĖ {0}`. -/
noncomputable def sqgBox (n : ‚Ąē) : Finset (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) :=
  ((Fintype.piFinset fun _ : Fin 2 =>
      Finset.Icc (-((n : ‚Ą§) + 1)) ((n : ‚Ą§) + 1)) : Finset (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)).erase 0

/-- Membership in `sqgBox n` via the per-coordinate `‚Ąď‚ąě` bound. -/
theorem mem_sqgBox_iff {n : ‚Ąē} {m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§} :
    m ‚ąą sqgBox n ‚ÜĒ m ‚Č† 0 ‚ąß ‚ąÄ i : Fin 2, |m i| ‚Č§ (n : ‚Ą§) + 1 := by
  unfold sqgBox
  simp only [Finset.mem_erase, Fintype.mem_piFinset, Finset.mem_Icc]
  constructor
  ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®hne, hpi‚ü©
    refine ‚ü®hne, fun i => ?_‚ü©
    have := hpi i
    rcases this with ‚ü®h1, h2‚ü©
    exact abs_le.mpr ‚ü®h1, h2‚ü©
  ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®hne, hpi‚ü©
    refine ‚ü®hne, fun i => ?_‚ü©
    have := hpi i
    exact ‚ü®(abs_le.mp this).1, (abs_le.mp this).2‚ü©

/-- `0 ‚ąČ sqgBox n`. -/
theorem zero_not_mem_sqgBox (n : ‚Ąē) : (0 : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚ąČ sqgBox n := by
  unfold sqgBox
  simp

/-- `sqgBox n` is symmetric under negation. -/
theorem sqgBox_symmetric (n : ‚Ąē) : IsSymmetricSupport (sqgBox n) := by
  intro m hm
  rw [mem_sqgBox_iff] at hm ‚äĘ
  refine ‚ü®?_, ?_‚ü©
  ¬∑ intro h
    apply hm.1
    have := congrArg (Neg.neg) h
    simpa [neg_zero, neg_neg] using this
  ¬∑ intro i
    rw [show (-m) i = -(m i) from rfl, abs_neg]
    exact hm.2 i

/-- `sqgBox` is monotone in `n`. -/
theorem sqgBox_mono (n : ‚Ąē) : sqgBox n ‚äÜ sqgBox (n + 1) := by
  intro m hm
  rw [mem_sqgBox_iff] at hm ‚äĘ
  refine ‚ü®hm.1, fun i => ?_‚ü©
  calc |m i| ‚Č§ (n : ‚Ą§) + 1 := hm.2 i
    _ ‚Č§ ((n + 1 : ‚Ąē) : ‚Ą§) + 1 := by push_cast; linarith

/-- Every nonzero mode eventually enters `sqgBox n`. -/
theorem exists_mem_sqgBox {m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§} (hm : m ‚Č† 0) :
    ‚ąÉ N : ‚Ąē, ‚ąÄ n ‚Č• N, m ‚ąą sqgBox n := by
  refine ‚ü®(|m 0|.toNat) ‚äĒ (|m 1|.toNat), fun n hn => ?_‚ü©
  rw [mem_sqgBox_iff]
  refine ‚ü®hm, fun i => ?_‚ü©
  have hN1 : (|m 0|.toNat : ‚Ą§) ‚Č§ (n : ‚Ą§) := by exact_mod_cast le_of_max_le_left hn
  have hN2 : (|m 1|.toNat : ‚Ą§) ‚Č§ (n : ‚Ą§) := by exact_mod_cast le_of_max_le_right hn
  have h0 : |m 0| ‚Č§ (n : ‚Ą§) := by
    have heq : (|m 0|.toNat : ‚Ą§) = |m 0| := Int.toNat_of_nonneg (abs_nonneg _)
    linarith
  have h1 : |m 1| ‚Č§ (n : ‚Ą§) := by
    have heq : (|m 1|.toNat : ‚Ą§) = |m 1| := Int.toNat_of_nonneg (abs_nonneg _)
    linarith
  fin_cases i
  ¬∑ show |m 0| ‚Č§ (n : ‚Ą§) + 1; linarith
  ¬∑ show |m 1| ‚Č§ (n : ‚Ą§) + 1; linarith

/-! ### ¬ß10.119 Fourier-coefficient restriction onto `sqgBox n`

The restriction operator `fourierRestrict n őł : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n) ‚Üí ‚Ąā`
sends an `L¬≤(ūĚēč¬≤)` element `őł` to its Fourier coefficients on modes in
`sqgBox n`. This is the truncation that feeds the ¬ß10.116 Galerkin
capstone, with uniform ‚Ąď¬≤ bound from Parseval. -/

/-- **Fourier-coefficient restriction to `sqgBox n`.** -/
noncomputable def fourierRestrict
    (n : ‚Ąē) (őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))) :
    ‚Ü•(sqgBox n) ‚Üí ‚Ąā :=
  fun m => mFourierCoeff őł m.val

@[simp] theorem fourierRestrict_apply
    (n : ‚Ąē) (őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (m : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n)) :
    fourierRestrict n őł m = mFourierCoeff őł m.val := rfl

/-- `galerkinExtend` of a restricted vector reproduces the Fourier
coefficients of `őł` on modes in `sqgBox n`, and `0` elsewhere. -/
theorem galerkinExtend_fourierRestrict_apply
    [DecidableEq (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)]
    (n : ‚Ąē) (őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) :
    galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (fourierRestrict n őł) m
      = if m ‚ąą sqgBox n then mFourierCoeff őł m else 0 := by
  by_cases hm : m ‚ąą sqgBox n
  ¬∑ rw [galerkinExtend_apply_of_mem _ _ hm, if_pos hm]; rfl
  ¬∑ rw [galerkinExtend_apply_of_not_mem _ _ hm, if_neg hm]

/-- **Uniform ‚Ąď¬≤ bound for `fourierRestrict`.** The finite L¬≤-sum of
restricted Fourier coefficients is bounded by the full Parseval sum,
hence by the L¬≤ norm squared of `őł`. Uniform in `n`. -/
theorem sum_sq_fourierRestrict_le_L2Sq
    (n : ‚Ąē) (őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))) :
    (‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖfourierRestrict n őł m‚ÄĖ ^ 2) ‚Č§ ‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖőł x‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := by
  have hP : HasSum (fun k : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ => ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff őł k‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
      (‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖőł x‚ÄĖ ^ 2) := hasSum_sq_mFourierCoeff őł
  have hSumm : Summable (fun k : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ => ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff őł k‚ÄĖ ^ 2) :=
    hP.summable
  have hSubset : (‚ąĎ m ‚ąą sqgBox n, ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff őł m‚ÄĖ ^ 2) ‚Č§
      ‚ąĎ' k : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§, ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff őł k‚ÄĖ ^ 2 :=
    hSumm.sum_le_tsum (sqgBox n) (fun _ _ => sq_nonneg _)
  rw [hP.tsum_eq] at hSubset
  calc (‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖfourierRestrict n őł m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
      = ‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff őł m.val‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := by
        apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
        intros m _; rfl
    _ = ‚ąĎ m ‚ąą (sqgBox n).attach, ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff őł m.val‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := by
        rw [show ((Finset.univ : Finset ‚Ü•(sqgBox n))) = (sqgBox n).attach from
          Finset.univ_eq_attach (sqgBox n)]
    _ = ‚ąĎ m ‚ąą sqgBox n, ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff őł m‚ÄĖ ^ 2 :=
        Finset.sum_attach (sqgBox n)
          (fun m => ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff őł m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
    _ ‚Č§ ‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖőł x‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := hSubset

/-! ### ¬ß10.120 Real-symmetry of the restricted Fourier data

If `őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (ūĚēč¬≤)` has real-symmetric Fourier coefficients (i.e.
`mFourierCoeff őł (-m) = star (mFourierCoeff őł m)` for every `m`), then
the restricted vector `fourierRestrict n őł` satisfies the
`IsRealCoeff`-style hypothesis required by ¬ß10.116. -/

/-- **Real-symmetric-Fourier predicate on `Lp ‚Ąā 2`.** Encodes the
condition that `őł` corresponds to a real-valued function on `ūĚēč¬≤`. -/
def IsFourierRealSym
    (őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))) : Prop :=
  ‚ąÄ m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§, mFourierCoeff őł (-m) = star (mFourierCoeff őł m)

/-- **Real-symmetry of the restricted vector.** Given `IsFourierRealSym őł`,
`galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (fourierRestrict n őł)` satisfies the
`hRealC‚āÄ`-hypothesis of ¬ß10.116. -/
theorem galerkinExtend_fourierRestrict_realSym
    [DecidableEq (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)]
    {n : ‚Ąē} {őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    (hőł : IsFourierRealSym őł) :
    ‚ąÄ m ‚ąą sqgBox n,
      galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (fourierRestrict n őł) (-m) =
        star (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (fourierRestrict n őł) m) := by
  intro m hm
  have hnegm : -m ‚ąą sqgBox n := sqgBox_symmetric n m hm
  rw [galerkinExtend_fourierRestrict_apply, galerkinExtend_fourierRestrict_apply,
      if_pos hnegm, if_pos hm]
  exact hőł m

/-! ### ¬ß10.121 Per-level time-global Galerkin trajectory from `L¬≤` data

For an `L¬≤` initial datum `őł‚āÄ` with real-symmetric Fourier coefficients,
¬ß10.116 produces a time-global Galerkin trajectory `őĪ‚āô` on each
`sqgBox n` with initial data `fourierRestrict n őł‚āÄ`. The radius `R` is
picked uniform in `n` via the Parseval bound: any `R` with
`(R/2)¬≤ ‚Č• ‚ąę ‚ÄĖőł‚āÄ‚ÄĖ¬≤` works for every `n`. -/

/-- **Per-level Galerkin trajectory.** Given `őł‚āÄ` with real-symmetric
Fourier coefficients, for each `n` there is a Galerkin trajectory `őĪ‚āô`
on `sqgBox n` starting from the restricted data, with the full
5-way conjunction of ¬ß10.116.H.3: derivative, ‚Ąď¬≤-sum conservation,
real-symmetry propagation, and uniform ŌÄ-norm bound. The ŌÄ-norm bound
constant `R/2` is UNIFORM in `n`. -/
theorem exists_galerkin_trajectory_of_L2
    [DecidableEq (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)]
    (őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (hőł : IsFourierRealSym őł)
    {R : ‚ĄĚ} (hR : 0 < R)
    (hR2 : (R / 2) ^ 2 ‚Č• ‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖőł x‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
    (n : ‚Ąē) :
    ‚ąÉ őĪ : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (‚Ü•(sqgBox n) ‚Üí ‚Ąā), őĪ 0 = fourierRestrict n őł ‚ąß
      (‚ąÄ t, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
        HasDerivWithinAt őĪ (galerkinVectorField (sqgBox n) (őĪ t))
          (Set.Ici (0 : ‚ĄĚ)) t) ‚ąß
      (‚ąÄ t, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
        (‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖőĪ t m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
          = ‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖfourierRestrict n őł m‚ÄĖ ^ 2) ‚ąß
      (‚ąÄ t, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí ‚ąÄ k ‚ąą sqgBox n,
        galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (őĪ t) (-k)
          = star (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (őĪ t) k)) ‚ąß
      (‚ąÄ t, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí ‚ÄĖőĪ t‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ R / 2) := by
  have hBound : (‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖfourierRestrict n őł m‚ÄĖ ^ 2) ‚Č§ (R / 2) ^ 2 :=
    le_trans (sum_sq_fourierRestrict_le_L2Sq n őł) hR2
  exact galerkin_time_global_unconditional_realSym (sqgBox n) (sqgBox_symmetric n)
    hR (fourierRestrict n őł) hBound
    (galerkinExtend_fourierRestrict_realSym hőł)

/-! ### ¬ß10.122 Uniform L¬≤ bound on the lifted Galerkin trajectory

For each level `n`, define `őł‚āô(t) := galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (őĪ‚āô t)`.
Combining ¬ß10.117.A with the ‚Ąď¬≤-sum conservation of ¬ß10.116 and the
Parseval bound of ¬ß10.119 produces
`hsSeminormSq 0 (őł‚āô t) ‚Č§ ‚ąę ‚ÄĖőł‚āÄ‚ÄĖ¬≤`, **uniformly in `n` and `t`**. -/

/-- **Uniform L¬≤ bound for the lifted trajectory.** `hsSeminormSq 0`
of `galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (őĪ‚āô t)` is bounded by the L¬≤ norm squared
of the original data `őł`, uniformly in `n` and `t ‚Č• 0`. -/
theorem hsSeminormSq_galerkinToLp_le_L2Sq
    [DecidableEq (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)]
    (őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (n : ‚Ąē)
    (őĪ : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (‚Ü•(sqgBox n) ‚Üí ‚Ąā))
    (hEnergy : ‚ąÄ t, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
      (‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖőĪ t m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
        = ‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖfourierRestrict n őł m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
    {t : ‚ĄĚ} (ht : 0 ‚Č§ t) :
    hsSeminormSq 0 (galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (őĪ t)) ‚Č§ ‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖőł x‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := by
  rw [hsSeminormSq_zero_galerkinToLp (zero_not_mem_sqgBox n)]
  calc (‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖőĪ t m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
      = ‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖfourierRestrict n őł m‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := hEnergy t ht
    _ ‚Č§ ‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖőł x‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := sum_sq_fourierRestrict_le_L2Sq n őł

/-! ### ¬ß10.123 Per-mode uniform bound on the Galerkin coefficients

For every fixed mode `m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§`, the scalar time-dependent
Fourier coefficient `galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (őĪ‚āô t) m` is bounded,
uniformly in `n` and `t ‚Č• 0`, by `‚ąö(‚ąę ‚ÄĖőł‚āÄ‚ÄĖ¬≤)`. This is the per-mode
L‚ąě control that feeds the diagonal subsequence argument for the
weak-* limit. -/

/-- **Per-mode uniform bound.** `‚ÄĖgalerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (őĪ‚āô t) m‚ÄĖ¬≤`
is bounded by `‚ąę ‚ÄĖőł‚āÄ‚ÄĖ¬≤`, uniformly in `n`, `t ‚Č• 0`, and `m`. -/
theorem sq_galerkinExtend_le_L2Sq
    [DecidableEq (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)]
    (őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (n : ‚Ąē)
    (őĪ : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (‚Ü•(sqgBox n) ‚Üí ‚Ąā))
    (hEnergy : ‚ąÄ t, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
      (‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖőĪ t m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
        = ‚ąĎ m : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖfourierRestrict n őł m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
    {t : ‚ĄĚ} (ht : 0 ‚Č§ t) (m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) :
    ‚ÄĖgalerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (őĪ t) m‚ÄĖ ^ 2 ‚Č§ ‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖőł x‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := by
  by_cases hm : m ‚ąą sqgBox n
  ¬∑ rw [galerkinExtend_apply_of_mem _ _ hm]
    have hSumLe : (‚ąĎ k : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖőĪ t k‚ÄĖ ^ 2) ‚Č§ ‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖőł x‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := by
      calc (‚ąĎ k : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖőĪ t k‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
          = ‚ąĎ k : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖfourierRestrict n őł k‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := hEnergy t ht
        _ ‚Č§ ‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖőł x‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := sum_sq_fourierRestrict_le_L2Sq n őł
    have hMember : ‚ÄĖőĪ t ‚ü®m, hm‚ü©‚ÄĖ ^ 2 ‚Č§ ‚ąĎ k : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n), ‚ÄĖőĪ t k‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := by
      have hNn : ‚ąÄ k ‚ąą (Finset.univ : Finset ‚Ü•(sqgBox n)),
          0 ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖőĪ t k‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := fun _ _ => sq_nonneg _
      exact Finset.single_le_sum (f := fun k : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n) => ‚ÄĖőĪ t k‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
        hNn (Finset.mem_univ _)
    linarith
  ¬∑ rw [galerkinExtend_apply_of_not_mem _ _ hm, norm_zero, pow_two, mul_zero]
    exact integral_nonneg (fun x => sq_nonneg _)

/-! ### ¬ß10.124 Galerkin ‚Üí full-SQG weak-limit program status

The S‚āô ‚Üó truncation infrastructure of ¬ß10.118‚Äď¬ß10.123 supplies the
uniform estimates classically used to extract a weak-* L¬≤(ūĚēč¬≤) limit
of the Galerkin approximants:

* ¬ß10.118 ‚ÄĒ nested symmetric, zero-excluding supports exhausting ‚Ą§¬≤ ‚ąĖ {0}.
* ¬ß10.119 ‚ÄĒ `fourierRestrict` + Parseval-derived uniform ‚Ąď¬≤ bound.
* ¬ß10.120 ‚ÄĒ real-symmetry of restricted Fourier data inherited from
  `IsFourierRealSym őł`.
* ¬ß10.121 ‚ÄĒ per-level time-global Galerkin trajectory from ¬ß10.116
  with a uniform-in-`n` ŌÄ-norm bound `R/2`.
* ¬ß10.122 ‚ÄĒ `hsSeminormSq 0 (őł‚āô t) ‚Č§ ‚ąę ‚ÄĖőł‚ÄĖ¬≤` uniformly in `n, t`.
* ¬ß10.123 ‚ÄĒ per-mode pointwise bound `‚ÄĖőł‚āôŐā(m, t)‚ÄĖ¬≤ ‚Č§ ‚ąę ‚ÄĖőł‚ÄĖ¬≤`.

¬ß10.125 onward then formalizes the compactness and passage-to-the-
limit argument in a structural (hypothesis-keyed) form, pushing the
last genuinely open ingredient ‚ÄĒ a per-mode time-modulus of
continuity derived from a uniform bound on the Galerkin RHS ‚ÄĒ into
a single named hypothesis `IsGalerkinLimitData`. -/

/-! ### ¬ß10.125 `IsGalerkinLimitData` ‚ÄĒ structural packaging of the limit

For generic `L¬≤(ūĚēč¬≤)` initial data the classical Galerkin ‚Üí full-SQG
limit relies on a per-mode time-modulus of continuity that is not
automatic from the `L¬≤` norm alone: it consumes either an `ŠłĘ¬Ļ`-type
bound on the Galerkin trajectory or an `H‚ĀĽ¬≤` test-function duality
(Resnick weak solutions). To factor that last ingredient out of the
structural chain, we package every datum produced by a successful
diagonal extraction into a `IsGalerkinLimitData` predicate. The
predicate bundles:

* a limit coefficient function `b : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ‚Ąā`;
* consistency with the initial data: `b m 0 = mFourierCoeff őł m`
  for every `m ‚Č† 0`, and `b 0 t = 0` for every `t ‚Č• 0`;
* ‚Ąď¬≤ summability uniformly in `t ‚Č• 0`, with the `‚ąę ‚ÄĖőł‚ÄĖ¬≤` upper bound;
* ‚Ąď¬≤-sum conservation: `‚ąĎ ‚ÄĖb m t‚ÄĖ¬≤ = ‚ąĎ ‚ÄĖb m 0‚ÄĖ¬≤` for every `t ‚Č• 0`;
* real-symmetry: `b (-m) t = star (b m t)`.

The predicate is satisfied (uncondit¬≠ionally) by the `t ‚Ü¶ 0`
trajectory when `őł = 0`, and by any data supplied by a classical
Resnick-style extraction. Downstream sections (¬ß10.126‚Äď¬ß10.130)
consume the predicate to build the `SqgSolution`, transferring all
of ¬ß10.118‚Äď¬ß10.123's uniform estimates through the limit. -/

/-- **Galerkin-limit data structure.** Packages the output of a
diagonal-subsequence extraction of the ¬ß10.121 per-level Galerkin
family into a single per-mode coefficient function, with the
uniform-in-time invariants inherited from ¬ß10.116 / ¬ß10.117. -/
structure IsGalerkinLimitData
    (őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (b : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ‚Ąā) : Prop where
  /-- Zero-mode triviality at every time (consistent with `0 ‚ąČ sqgBox n`). -/
  zeroMode : ‚ąÄ t, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí b 0 t = 0
  /-- Initial data matches the Fourier coefficients of `őł`. -/
  initial : ‚ąÄ m, b m 0 = mFourierCoeff őł m
  /-- ‚Ąď¬≤ summability of the limit coefficients at every forward time. -/
  summable : ‚ąÄ t, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí Summable (fun m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ => ‚ÄĖb m t‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
  /-- ‚Ąď¬≤ conservation: `‚ąĎ' m, ‚ÄĖb m t‚ÄĖ¬≤ = ‚ąĎ' m, ‚ÄĖb m 0‚ÄĖ¬≤`. -/
  conservation : ‚ąÄ t, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
    (‚ąĎ' m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§, ‚ÄĖb m t‚ÄĖ ^ 2) = ‚ąĎ' m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§, ‚ÄĖb m 0‚ÄĖ ^ 2
  /-- Real-symmetry of the limit coefficients. -/
  realSym : ‚ąÄ t, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí ‚ąÄ m, b (-m) t = star (b m t)

/-- **The zero Galerkin-limit data structure.** Witnesses
`IsGalerkinLimitData` for the zero `L¬≤` element with `b ‚Č° 0`. -/
theorem IsGalerkinLimitData.ofZero :
    IsGalerkinLimitData
      (0 : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
      (fun _ _ => (0 : ‚Ąā)) where
  zeroMode := fun _ _ => rfl
  initial := fun m => (mFourierCoeff_zero m).symm
  summable := fun _ _ => by
    convert summable_zero with m
    simp
  conservation := fun _ _ => rfl
  realSym := fun _ _ _ => by simp

/-! ### ¬ß10.126 Fourier synthesis of the limit data into `L¬≤(ūĚēč¬≤)`

Given `IsGalerkinLimitData őł b`, the Fourier series
`‚ąĎ m, b m t ‚ÄĘ mFourierLp 2 m` converges in `L¬≤(ūĚēč¬≤)` at every `t ‚Č• 0`
thanks to the ‚Ąď¬≤ summability clause. Define the limit trajectory
`őł_lim t := this series`. -/

/-- **Forward synthesis map** taking a limit coefficient function at
a single time slice to an `L¬≤(ūĚēč¬≤)` element. Uses the `galerkinToLp`
lift on a finite truncation, cohered into a tsum in `L¬≤ via the
‚Ąď¬≤ summability hypothesis. This is the structural analog of the
"Fourier inverse of a ‚Ąď¬≤ sequence" operation. To avoid importing
abstract Hilbert-space synthesis from mathlib, we define the map
implicitly via its Fourier coefficients and package the existence
claim as an additional hypothesis in ¬ß10.127. -/
def galerkinLimitHasFourierCoeff
    (b : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąā)
    (őł_t : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))) : Prop :=
  ‚ąÄ m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§, mFourierCoeff őł_t m = b m

/-- **`hsSeminormSq 0` bound from the ‚Ąď¬≤-sum on a full-domain series.**
If `őł_t : Lp ‚Ąā 2` has its Fourier coefficients identified with a
‚Ąď¬≤-summable function `b` via `galerkinLimitHasFourierCoeff`, and the
zeroth coefficient vanishes (`b 0 = 0`), then `hsSeminormSq 0 (őł_t)`
equals the tsum of `‚ÄĖb m‚ÄĖ¬≤` over all modes. -/
theorem hsSeminormSq_zero_of_fourierCoeff_eq
    (b : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąā)
    (őł_t : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (hCoeff : galerkinLimitHasFourierCoeff b őł_t)
    (hZero : b 0 = 0) :
    hsSeminormSq 0 őł_t = ‚ąĎ' m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§, ‚ÄĖb m‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := by
  unfold hsSeminormSq
  apply tsum_congr
  intro m
  by_cases hm : m = 0
  ¬∑ subst hm
    rw [hZero, norm_zero]
    simp
  ¬∑ rw [fracDerivSymbol_of_ne_zero 0 hm, Real.rpow_zero, one_pow, one_mul,
      hCoeff m]

/-! ### ¬ß10.127 Packaged limit trajectory ‚ÄĒ existence hypothesis

Take `IsGalerkinLimitData őł b` as given, together with a per-time
Fourier-synthesis witness `őł_lim : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2` whose coefficients
match `b`. All downstream `SqgSolution` structure then follows
algebraically. -/

/-- **Limit `Lp`-trajectory with prescribed Fourier coefficients.**
Packages `b` and a trajectory `őł_lim` whose `mFourierCoeff` at every
mode equals `b m t`. -/
structure GalerkinLimitTrajectory
    (őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (b : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ‚Ąā) where
  /-- The synthesized `L¬≤` trajectory. -/
  őł_lim : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))
  /-- Fourier coefficients at every time match `b`. -/
  coeff : ‚ąÄ t, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí ‚ąÄ m, mFourierCoeff (őł_lim t) m = b m t
  /-- Initial-time slice matches `őł`. -/
  init_eq : őł_lim 0 = őł

/-- **Zero trajectory instantiates a Galerkin limit over the zero datum.** -/
noncomputable def GalerkinLimitTrajectory.ofZero :
    GalerkinLimitTrajectory
      (0 : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
      (fun _ _ => (0 : ‚Ąā)) where
  őł_lim := fun _ => 0
  coeff := fun _ _ m => by simp [mFourierCoeff]
  init_eq := rfl

/-! ### ¬ß10.128 `SqgEvolutionAxioms` for a packaged limit trajectory

Given `IsGalerkinLimitData őł b` + `GalerkinLimitTrajectory őł b` (with
`hCoeffs : ‚ąÄ m, mFourierCoeff (őł_lim t) m = b m t`), the limit
trajectory satisfies `SqgEvolutionAxioms`. `l2Conservation`,
`meanConservation` are pure Fourier-side consequences of the
hypotheses. `velocityIsRieszTransform` uses the standard time-
independent Riesz multiplier ‚ÄĒ packaged via `IsSqgVelocityComponent`
applied to a `trigPoly`-like synthesis of the per-time velocity;
for the structural skeleton here, we supply the zero velocity when
`őł ‚Č° 0` and inherit the velocity from a supplied structural
assumption otherwise. -/

/-- **Velocity-witness hypothesis.** A time-indexed family
`u : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2` realising the SQG velocity of `őł_lim`
mode-by-mode (same shape as `SqgEvolutionAxioms.velocityIsRieszTransform`). -/
def HasGalerkinLimitVelocity
    (őł_lim : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (u : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))) : Prop :=
  ‚ąÄ (j : Fin 2) (t : ‚ĄĚ), IsSqgVelocityComponent (őł_lim t) (u j t) j

/-- **Zero velocity witnesses the zero trajectory.** -/
theorem HasGalerkinLimitVelocity.ofZero :
    HasGalerkinLimitVelocity
      (őł_lim := fun _ : ‚ĄĚ => (0 : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))))
      (u := fun _ _ => 0) := by
  intros j t
  exact IsSqgVelocityComponent.of_zero j

/-- **`SqgEvolutionAxioms` for a packaged Galerkin-limit trajectory.**

Assumes:
* `IsGalerkinLimitData őł b` ‚ÄĒ the abstract limit data.
* `GalerkinLimitTrajectory őł b` ‚ÄĒ a synthesized `L¬≤` trajectory with
  matching Fourier coefficients.
* `HasGalerkinLimitVelocity őł_lim u` ‚ÄĒ a Riesz-transform velocity
  witness for the trajectory.

Concludes `SqgEvolutionAxioms őł_lim`. The three clauses are
discharged structurally: L¬≤-conservation from
`hsSeminormSq_zero_of_fourierCoeff_eq` + `IsGalerkinLimitData.conservation`,
mean-conservation from `IsGalerkinLimitData.zeroMode` +
`IsGalerkinLimitData.initial`, and the velocity existence from the
supplied witness. -/
theorem SqgEvolutionAxioms.of_galerkinLimit
    {őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    {b : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ‚Ąā}
    (hData : IsGalerkinLimitData őł b)
    (traj : GalerkinLimitTrajectory őł b)
    {u : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    (hu : HasGalerkinLimitVelocity traj.őł_lim u) :
    SqgEvolutionAxioms traj.őł_lim where
  l2Conservation := fun t ht => by
    have hCoeff_t : galerkinLimitHasFourierCoeff (fun m => b m t) (traj.őł_lim t) :=
      fun m => traj.coeff t ht m
    have hCoeff_0 : galerkinLimitHasFourierCoeff (fun m => b m 0) (traj.őł_lim 0) :=
      fun m => traj.coeff 0 le_rfl m
    rw [hsSeminormSq_zero_of_fourierCoeff_eq _ _ hCoeff_t (hData.zeroMode t ht),
        hsSeminormSq_zero_of_fourierCoeff_eq _ _ hCoeff_0 (hData.zeroMode 0 le_rfl)]
    exact hData.conservation t ht
  meanConservation := fun t ht => by
    rw [traj.coeff t ht 0, traj.coeff 0 le_rfl 0, hData.zeroMode t ht,
        hData.zeroMode 0 le_rfl]
  velocityIsRieszTransform := fun j => ‚ü®u j, fun t => hu j t‚ü©

/-! ### ¬ß10.129 Capstone: `SqgSolution` from a packaged Galerkin limit

Assembling ¬ß10.128's `SqgEvolutionAxioms` with an HňĘ summability
