theorem HasModeLipschitzFamily.modeCoeff_eq_galerkinExtend
    {őĪ : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (‚Ü•(sqgBox n) ‚Üí ‚Ąā)}
    (lip : HasModeLipschitzFamily őĪ)
    (n : ‚Ąē) (t : ‚ĄĚ) (m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) :
    lip.modeCoeff n t m = galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (őĪ n t) m := by
  by_cases hm : m ‚ąą sqgBox n
  ¬∑ rw [lip.modeCoeff_eq n t m hm, galerkinExtend_apply_of_mem _ _ hm]
  ¬∑ rw [lip.modeCoeff_off n t m hm,
        galerkinExtend_apply_of_not_mem _ _ hm]

/-- **¬ß10.155.B  `HasPerModeLimit.ofModeLipschitzFamily` constructor.**
Assembles `HasPerModeLimit őĪ` from `HasModeLipschitzFamily őĪ` +
a classical Arzel√†‚ÄďAscoli + Cantor diagonal extraction witness
`(nsub, b)`.  The witness asserts that the `galerkinExtend`-valued
per-mode sequence converges pointwise-in-`t` at every mode
`m ‚ąą Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§` and every `t ‚Č• 0`.

This is the structural reduction of Target #1: given the
`HasModeLipschitzFamily` data (which supplies the equicontinuity
and uniform-boundedness hypotheses of Arzel√†‚ÄďAscoli), the remaining
