/-! ### ¬ß10.157 Fourier synthesis from ‚Ąď¬≤-summable coefficients

Mathlib's `mFourierBasis` is a `HilbertBasis (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Ąā` on
`L¬≤(ūĚēč¬≤)`; its representation map `mFourierBasis.repr` is a linear
isometry equivalence into `lp (fun _ : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ => ‚Ąā) 2`.  Its inverse
gives the Fourier-synthesis map: from an ‚Ąď¬≤-summable coefficient
sequence, construct the corresponding `Lp` element.

¬ß10.157 supplies the concrete `őł_lim t` operator that discharges the
`őł_lim` input of `HasFourierSynthesis.ofPerModeLimit` (¬ß10.154.B), as
long as the per-mode limit `per.b ¬∑ t` is ‚Ąď¬≤-summable at every `t ‚Č• 0`
(which follows from the uniform `L¬≤` bound on the Galerkin sequence +
Fatou on `‚Ąď¬≤(‚Ą§¬≤)`). -/

/-- **¬ß10.157.A  Fourier synthesis `Lp` element from an ‚Ąď¬≤ sequence.**
Lifts `b ‚ąą ‚Ąď¬≤(‚Ą§¬≤)` to the corresponding `L¬≤(ūĚēč¬≤)` element via
`mFourierBasis.repr.symm`. -/
noncomputable def fourierSynthesisLp
    (b : lp (fun _ : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ => ‚Ąā) 2) :
    Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))) :=
  mFourierBasis.repr.symm b

/-- **¬ß10.157.B  Fourier coefficients of the Fourier synthesis recover
the input sequence.**  `mFourierCoeff (fourierSynthesisLp b) m = b m`
for every mode `m`. -/
theorem mFourierCoeff_fourierSynthesisLp
    (b : lp (fun _ : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ => ‚Ąā) 2) (m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) :
    mFourierCoeff (fourierSynthesisLp b) m = b m := by
  have h_repr : mFourierBasis.repr (fourierSynthesisLp b) = b := by
    unfold fourierSynthesisLp
    exact LinearIsometryEquiv.apply_symm_apply _ _
  have := congrArg (fun (v : lp (fun _ : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ => ‚Ąā) 2) => v m) h_repr
  simp only [mFourierBasis_repr] at this
  exact this

