/-- **¬ß10.158.A  Concrete `őł_lim` operator via Fourier synthesis.**
Given an `lp (fun _ : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ => ‚Ąā) 2`-valued function `bLp` of time,
produces the corresponding `Lp ‚Ąā 2`-valued trajectory via pointwise
Fourier synthesis. -/
noncomputable def őłLimOfLp
    (bLp : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí lp (fun _ : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ => ‚Ąā) 2) :
    ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))) :=
  fun t => fourierSynthesisLp (bLp t)

/-- **¬ß10.158.C  `lp` element from summable-square-norm sequence.**
Builds the `lp (fun _ : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ => ‚Ąā) 2` element whose underlying
function is `b`, given that `Summable (fun m => ‚ÄĖb m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)`.  Uses
mathlib's `mem‚Ąďp_gen_iff` (which states `Mem‚Ąďp f p ‚ÜĒ Summable (fun i =>
‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ ^ p.toReal)` for `0 < p.toReal`).  Supplies the elementary link
from per-mode ‚Ąď¬≤ summability to the `lp`-valued input of `őłLimOfLp`. -/
