/-! ### ¬ß10.160 Parseval on a difference ‚ÄĒ building block for strong-L¬≤

The strong-`L¬≤` convergence proof in `HasFourierSynthesis.ofSummable`
(¬ß10.159.C) needs to express `‚ąę ‚ÄĖf - g‚ÄĖ¬≤` as a per-mode sum of
squared Fourier-coefficient differences.  This is Parseval applied to
`f - g`, combined with the linearity
`mFourierCoeff (f - g) m = mFourierCoeff f m - mFourierCoeff g m`.

¬ß10.160 factors this as a standalone lemma so later discharges of
`h_L2` can consume it directly, without re-deriving the Parseval
step each time. -/

/-- **¬ß10.160  Parseval on a difference.**  For any two `L¬≤(ūĚēč¬≤)`
elements `f, g`:
`‚ąę ‚ÄĖf x - g x‚ÄĖ¬≤ dx = ‚ąĎ' m, ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff f m - mFourierCoeff g m‚ÄĖ¬≤`. -/
theorem integral_norm_sq_sub_eq_tsum_sq_mFourierCoeff_sub
    (f g : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))) :
    (‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖf x - g x‚ÄĖ ^ 2) =
    ‚ąĎ' m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§, ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff f m - mFourierCoeff g m‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := by
  -- Parseval on `(f - g)` at the `Lp` level.
  have h_pars : HasSum (fun m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ => ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (f - g) m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
      (‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖ(f - g) x‚ÄĖ ^ 2) := hasSum_sq_mFourierCoeff (f - g)
  -- Linearity of `mFourierCoeff` on the difference via `mFourierCoeffLM`.
  have h_sub : ‚ąÄ m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§,
      mFourierCoeff (f - g) m = mFourierCoeff f m - mFourierCoeff g m := by
    intro m
    show mFourierCoeffLM m (f - g) = mFourierCoeffLM m f - mFourierCoeffLM m g
    rw [map_sub]
  -- `‚ÄĖ(f - g) x‚ÄĖ¬≤ = ‚ÄĖf x - g x‚ÄĖ¬≤` a.e. (via `Lp` subtraction coercion).
  have h_ae : (fun x => ‚ÄĖ(f - g) x‚ÄĖ ^ 2) =ŠĶź[volume]
      fun x => ‚ÄĖf x - g x‚ÄĖ ^ 2 := by
    filter_upwards [Lp.coeFn_sub f g] with x hx
    rw [hx, Pi.sub_apply]
  -- Integrals agree by a.e. equality.
  have h_int_eq : (‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖ(f - g) x‚ÄĖ ^ 2) = ‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖf x - g x‚ÄĖ ^ 2 :=
    integral_congr_ae h_ae
  rw [‚Üź h_int_eq, ‚Üź h_pars.tsum_eq]
  exact tsum_congr (fun m => by rw [h_sub m])

/-! ### ¬ß10.161 Galerkin-to-`őłLim` squared difference as per-mode ‚Ąď¬≤ sum

Combines ¬ß10.160 (Parseval on a difference) with
`mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp` (existing) and
`mFourierCoeff_őłLimOfSummable` (¬ß10.159.B) to express the squared
`L¬≤`-norm of the difference between the extracted Galerkin truncation
