/-! ### ¬ß10.163 Pure ‚Ąď¬≤ Vitali convergence ‚ÄĒ tight-family convergence

¬ß10.162 reduced the `h_L2` input of ¬ß10.159.C to a per-mode ‚Ąď¬≤ Tendsto
statement.  ¬ß10.163 is the general-‚Ąď¬≤ Vitali lemma that closes that
Tendsto from two elementary ingredients:

* **Per-mode convergence**: `f k i ‚Üí g i` pointwise in `k` at each `i`.
* **Uniform ‚Ąď¬≤-tail tightness on the differences**: for every `őĶ > 0`
  there is a finite `F : Finset őĻ` such that the tail of the
  squared-difference ‚Ąď¬≤ sum is `‚Č§ őĶ` **uniformly in `k`**.

Together these imply `‚ąĎ' i, ‚ÄĖf k i - g i‚ÄĖ¬≤ ‚Üí 0` as `k ‚Üí ‚ąě`.  The proof
splits the full tsum at `F` using `Summable.sum_add_tsum_subtype_compl`,
bounds the finite part via `tendsto_finset_sum` on pointwise convergence,
and bounds the tail by the tightness hypothesis.

The statement is free of SQG-specifics so the lemma lives in the pure
‚Ąď¬≤ layer.  ¬ß10.164 below specialises it back to the Galerkin setting. -/

/-- **¬ß10.163  Vitali ‚Ąď¬≤ convergence on squared differences.**  Per-mode
pointwise convergence `f k ¬∑ ‚Üí g` plus uniform ‚Ąď¬≤-tail tightness on the
squared differences (őĶ-Finset `F` bounding the tail ‚Č§ őĶ for every `k`)
plus summability of each squared-difference family gives
`‚ąĎ' i, ‚ÄĖf k i - g i‚ÄĖ¬≤ ‚Üí 0` as `k ‚Üí ‚ąě`. -/
theorem tsum_sq_sub_tendsto_zero_of_tight
    {őĻ : Type*} {f : ‚Ąē ‚Üí őĻ ‚Üí ‚Ąā} {g : őĻ ‚Üí ‚Ąā}
    (h_ptw : ‚ąÄ i, Filter.Tendsto (fun k => f k i) Filter.atTop (nhds (g i)))
    (h_sum_diff : ‚ąÄ k, Summable fun i => ‚ÄĖf k i - g i‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
    (h_tight : ‚ąÄ őĶ : ‚ĄĚ, 0 < őĶ ‚Üí ‚ąÉ F : Finset őĻ, ‚ąÄ k : ‚Ąē,
      (‚ąĎ' i : { i // i ‚ąČ F }, ‚ÄĖf k i.val - g i.val‚ÄĖ ^ 2) ‚Č§ őĶ) :
    Filter.Tendsto (fun k : ‚Ąē => ‚ąĎ' i, ‚ÄĖf k i - g i‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
      Filter.atTop (nhds 0) := by
  rw [Metric.tendsto_atTop]
  intro őĶ hőĶ
  have hőĶ2 : (0 : ‚ĄĚ) < őĶ / 2 := by linarith
  obtain ‚ü®F, hF‚ü© := h_tight (őĶ / 2) hőĶ2
  -- Per-mode squared differences tend to 0.
  have h_sq_ptw : ‚ąÄ i : őĻ,
      Filter.Tendsto (fun k => ‚ÄĖf k i - g i‚ÄĖ ^ 2) Filter.atTop (nhds 0) := by
    intro i
    have h1 : Filter.Tendsto (fun k => f k i - g i) Filter.atTop (nhds 0) := by
      simpa using (h_ptw i).sub_const (g i)
    have h2 : Filter.Tendsto (fun k => ‚ÄĖf k i - g i‚ÄĖ) Filter.atTop (nhds (0 : ‚ĄĚ)) := by
      simpa [norm_zero] using h1.norm
    simpa using h2.pow 2
  -- Finite sum of squared differences tends to 0.
  have h_sum_fin : Filter.Tendsto
      (fun k : ‚Ąē => ‚ąĎ i ‚ąą F, ‚ÄĖf k i - g i‚ÄĖ ^ 2) Filter.atTop (nhds 0) := by
    have := tendsto_finset_sum F (fun i (_ : i ‚ąą F) => h_sq_ptw i)
    simpa using this
  -- Extract `N` beyond which the finite sum is `< őĶ/2`.
  obtain ‚ü®N, hN‚ü© := Metric.tendsto_atTop.mp h_sum_fin (őĶ / 2) hőĶ2
  refine ‚ü®N, fun k hk => ?_‚ü©
  -- Split the full tsum at `F`.
  have hsplit : (‚ąĎ' i, ‚ÄĖf k i - g i‚ÄĖ ^ 2) =
      (‚ąĎ i ‚ąą F, ‚ÄĖf k i - g i‚ÄĖ ^ 2) +
      ‚ąĎ' i : { i // i ‚ąČ F }, ‚ÄĖf k i.val - g i.val‚ÄĖ ^ 2 :=
    ((h_sum_diff k).sum_add_tsum_subtype_compl F).symm
  -- Non-negativity of the various pieces.
  have h_total_nonneg : (0 : ‚ĄĚ) ‚Č§ ‚ąĎ' i, ‚ÄĖf k i - g i‚ÄĖ ^ 2 :=
    tsum_nonneg (fun _ => sq_nonneg _)
  have h_fin_nonneg : (0 : ‚ĄĚ) ‚Č§ ‚ąĎ i ‚ąą F, ‚ÄĖf k i - g i‚ÄĖ ^ 2 :=
    Finset.sum_nonneg (fun _ _ => sq_nonneg _)
  -- Bound the finite part by `őĶ/2`.
  have h_fin_bound : ‚ąĎ i ‚ąą F, ‚ÄĖf k i - g i‚ÄĖ ^ 2 < őĶ / 2 := by
    have := hN k hk
    rw [Real.dist_eq, sub_zero, abs_of_nonneg h_fin_nonneg] at this
    exact this
  -- Combine.
  rw [Real.dist_eq, sub_zero, abs_of_nonneg h_total_nonneg, hsplit]
  have h_tail_bound : (‚ąĎ' i : { i // i ‚ąČ F }, ‚ÄĖf k i.val - g i.val‚ÄĖ ^ 2) ‚Č§ őĶ / 2 := hF k
  linarith

/-! ### ¬ß10.164 `HasFourierSynthesis.ofTight` ‚ÄĒ drop-in capstone

Composes ¬ß10.159.C (`ofSummable`) with ¬ß10.162 (integral ‚Üí tsum reduction)
and ¬ß10.163 (tight-family ‚Ąď¬≤ Vitali convergence) into a single top-level
constructor that takes only elementary tight-family inputs.

Once the caller supplies per-mode summability (Fatou + uniform ‚Ąď¬≤ bound)
plus summability/tightness of the coefficient *differences*, the `h_L2`
hypothesis of ¬ß10.159.C is discharged entirely internally.  No `Lp`
coercion bookkeeping reaches the caller, and strong-`L¬≤` convergence is
produced from the pure ‚Ąď¬≤ Vitali argument of ¬ß10.163.

This is the maximally-closed form of `HasFourierSynthesis` construction
reachable without an additional compactness input: every non-structural
hypothesis is now an elementary ‚Ąď¬≤-level statement on the coefficient
sequence, with no `Lp`, `Parseval`, or `Fatou`-level analysis required
of the caller. -/

/-- **¬ß10.164  `HasFourierSynthesis.ofTight` ‚ÄĒ Tight-family capstone.**
Builds `HasFourierSynthesis per őł` from the four elementary ‚Ąď¬≤-level
inputs:

* `hInit_b` ‚ÄĒ initial coefficient match at `t = 0`.
* `hSum` ‚ÄĒ per-mode ‚Ąď¬≤-summability of `per.b ¬∑ t` at every `t ‚Č• 0`.
* `h_sum_diff` ‚ÄĒ per-mode ‚Ąď¬≤-summability of the Galerkin-to-limit
  coefficient differences at every `t ‚Č• 0` and `k : ‚Ąē`.
* `h_tight` ‚ÄĒ uniform ‚Ąď¬≤-tail tightness on those coefficient differences.

`h_L2` of ¬ß10.159.C is discharged internally via ¬ß10.162 + ¬ß10.163. -/
noncomputable def HasFourierSynthesis.ofTight
    {őĪ : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (‚Ü•(sqgBox n) ‚Üí ‚Ąā)}
    (per : HasPerModeLimit őĪ)
    {őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    (hInit_b : ‚ąÄ m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§, per.b m 0 = mFourierCoeff őł m)
    (hSum : ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
      Summable fun m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ => ‚ÄĖper.b m t‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
    (h_sum_diff : ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí ‚ąÄ k : ‚Ąē,
      Summable fun m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ =>
        ‚ÄĖgalerkinExtend (sqgBox (per.nsub k)) (őĪ (per.nsub k) t) m
          - per.b m t‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
    (h_tight : ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí ‚ąÄ őĶ : ‚ĄĚ, 0 < őĶ ‚Üí
      ‚ąÉ F : Finset (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§), ‚ąÄ k : ‚Ąē,
        (‚ąĎ' m : { m // m ‚ąČ F },
          ‚ÄĖgalerkinExtend (sqgBox (per.nsub k)) (őĪ (per.nsub k) t) m.val
            - per.b m.val t‚ÄĖ ^ 2) ‚Č§ őĶ) :
    HasFourierSynthesis per őł :=
  HasFourierSynthesis.ofSummable per hInit_b hSum
    (fun t ht =>
      tendsto_integral_norm_sq_galerkin_sub_őłLim_of_tsum per hSum
        (fun t' ht' =>
          tsum_sq_sub_tendsto_zero_of_tight
            (fun m => per.tendsto_modeCoeff m t' ht')
            (h_sum_diff t' ht')
            (h_tight t' ht'))
        t ht)

/-! ### ¬ß10.165.A Bolzano‚ÄďWeierstrass for bounded ‚Ąā-valued sequences

Wrapper around mathlib's `tendsto_subseq_of_bounded` specialised to the
proper metric space `‚Ąā`.  Every bounded sequence in `‚Ąā` admits a
convergent subsequence. -/

/-- **¬ß10.165.A  Bolzano‚ÄďWeierstrass on `‚Ąā`.**  Any sequence `s : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąā`
bounded in norm by some `M` has a strictly-monotone extractor `ŌÜ : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē`
and a limit `L : ‚Ąā` such that `s ‚ąė ŌÜ ‚Üí L`. -/
theorem exists_convergent_subseq_of_bounded_complex
    {s : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąā} (M : ‚ĄĚ) (hs : ‚ąÄ n, ‚ÄĖs n‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ M) :
    ‚ąÉ ŌÜ : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē, StrictMono ŌÜ ‚ąß ‚ąÉ L : ‚Ąā,
      Filter.Tendsto (fun k : ‚Ąē => s (ŌÜ k)) Filter.atTop (nhds L) := by
  have hB : Bornology.IsBounded (Metric.closedBall (0 : ‚Ąā) M) :=
    Metric.isBounded_closedBall
  have hIn : ‚ąÄ n, s n ‚ąą Metric.closedBall (0 : ‚Ąā) M := by
    intro n
    rw [Metric.mem_closedBall, dist_zero_right]
    exact hs n
  obtain ‚ü®L, _hL, ŌÜ, hŌÜ, htends‚ü© := tendsto_subseq_of_bounded hB hIn
  exact ‚ü®ŌÜ, hŌÜ, L, htends‚ü©

/-! ### ¬ß10.165.B Cantor diagonal for a countable family of bounded ‚Ąā-sequences

Given a countable family `s : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąā` with each row `s i ¬∑ `
uniformly bounded, classical Cantor diagonal across `i` produces one
strictly-monotone extractor `nsub : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē` such that `s i ‚ąė nsub`
converges for every `i`.

**Construction.**  Build stages `ő¶ : ‚Ąē ‚Üí (‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē)` with `ő¶ 0` the BW
extractor for `s 0` and `ő¶ (i+1) = ő¶ i ‚ąė Ōą_{i+1}` where `Ōą_{i+1}` is the
BW extractor of `s (i+1) ‚ąė ő¶ i`.  The diagonal `nsub k := ő¶ k k` is
strictly monotone (each `Ōą_j` is strictly monotone, so the stage
compositions preserve strict order on the diagonal), and for every `i`,
the tail `{nsub k : k ‚Č• i}` is a reindexing of `ő¶ i` through a
strictly-monotone function, so inherits convergence at row `i`. -/

/-- **¬ß10.165.B  Cantor diagonal.**  Given a countable family `s i : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąā`
of uniformly-bounded complex sequences, produce one subsequence extractor
`nsub : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē` with pointwise convergence along every row `i`. -/
theorem cantor_diagonal_complex
    (s : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąā)
    (hs : ‚ąÄ i : ‚Ąē, ‚ąÉ M : ‚ĄĚ, ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, ‚ÄĖs i n‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ M) :
    ‚ąÉ nsub : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē, StrictMono nsub ‚ąß
      ‚ąÉ L : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąā, ‚ąÄ i : ‚Ąē,
        Filter.Tendsto (fun k : ‚Ąē => s i (nsub k)) Filter.atTop (nhds (L i)) := by
  classical
  -- Helper: pick a BW extractor packaged as a strict-mono function + limit.
  let bwPick : ‚ąÄ (ŌÉ : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąā) (_ : ‚ąÉ M, ‚ąÄ n, ‚ÄĖŌÉ n‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ M),
      { p : (‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē) √ó ‚Ąā //
        StrictMono p.1 ‚ąß Filter.Tendsto (fun k => ŌÉ (p.1 k)) Filter.atTop (nhds p.2) } :=
    fun ŌÉ hŌÉ => Classical.indefiniteDescription _ (by
      obtain ‚ü®M, hM‚ü© := hŌÉ
      obtain ‚ü®ŌÜ, hŌÜ, L, hL‚ü© := exists_convergent_subseq_of_bounded_complex M hM
      exact ‚ü®(ŌÜ, L), hŌÜ, hL‚ü©)
  -- Define the stages recursively.  `stage i = (ő¶_i, L_i)` with `ő¶_i` strictMono,
  -- `Filter.Tendsto (s i ‚ąė ő¶_i) atTop (ūĚďĚ L_i)`, and `ő¶_(i+1) = ő¶_i ‚ąė Ōą_(i+1)`
  -- for `Ōą_(i+1)` the BW extractor of `s (i+1) ‚ąė ő¶_i`.
  let ő¶ : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē := fun i => Nat.rec
      ((bwPick (s 0) (hs 0)).val.1)
      (fun j prev =>
        prev ‚ąė (bwPick (fun k => s (j + 1) (prev k))
          (by obtain ‚ü®M, hM‚ü© := hs (j + 1); exact ‚ü®M, fun n => hM (prev n)‚ü©)).val.1)
      i
  let L : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąā := fun i => Nat.rec
      ((bwPick (s 0) (hs 0)).val.2)
      (fun j prev => (bwPick (fun k => s (j + 1) (ő¶ j k))
        (by obtain ‚ü®M, hM‚ü© := hs (j + 1); exact ‚ü®M, fun n => hM (ő¶ j n)‚ü©)).val.2)
      i
  -- Each ő¶ i is strictly monotone.
  have hő¶_mono : ‚ąÄ i, StrictMono (ő¶ i) := by
    intro i
    induction i with
    | zero => exact (bwPick (s 0) (hs 0)).property.1
    | succ j ih =>
      refine ih.comp ?_
      exact (bwPick (fun k => s (j + 1) (ő¶ j k))
        (by obtain ‚ü®M, hM‚ü© := hs (j + 1); exact ‚ü®M, fun n => hM (ő¶ j n)‚ü©)).property.1
  -- Stage 0 convergence.
  have hő¶0_tendsto : Filter.Tendsto (fun k => s 0 (ő¶ 0 k)) Filter.atTop (nhds (L 0)) :=
    (bwPick (s 0) (hs 0)).property.2
  -- Stage (i+1) convergence.
  have hő¶succ_tendsto : ‚ąÄ i,
      Filter.Tendsto (fun k => s (i + 1) (ő¶ (i + 1) k)) Filter.atTop (nhds (L (i + 1))) := by
    intro i
    -- By construction, ő¶ (i + 1) k = ő¶ i (Ōą_(i+1) k) where Ōą_(i+1) is the BW extractor.
    -- And L (i + 1) = limit of s (i+1) ‚ąė ő¶ i ‚ąė Ōą_(i+1).
    exact (bwPick (fun k => s (i + 1) (ő¶ i k))
      (by obtain ‚ü®M, hM‚ü© := hs (i + 1); exact ‚ü®M, fun n => hM (ő¶ i n)‚ü©)).property.2
  -- Consecutive stages: ő¶ (i+1) = ő¶ i ‚ąė Ōą for some strictMono Ōą.
  have hő¶_factor : ‚ąÄ i, ‚ąÉ Ōą : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē, StrictMono Ōą ‚ąß ő¶ (i + 1) = ő¶ i ‚ąė Ōą := by
    intro i
    refine ‚ü®(bwPick (fun k => s (i + 1) (ő¶ i k))
      (by obtain ‚ü®M, hM‚ü© := hs (i + 1); exact ‚ü®M, fun n => hM (ő¶ i n)‚ü©)).val.1,
      (bwPick (fun k => s (i + 1) (ő¶ i k))
        (by obtain ‚ü®M, hM‚ü© := hs (i + 1); exact ‚ü®M, fun n => hM (ő¶ i n)‚ü©)).property.1, rfl‚ü©
  -- Chain: for k ‚Č• i, ő¶ k = ő¶ i ‚ąė (some strictMono Ōą), via induction on (k - i).
  have hő¶_chain : ‚ąÄ i k, ‚ąÉ Ōą : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē, StrictMono Ōą ‚ąß ő¶ (i + k) = ő¶ i ‚ąė Ōą := by
    intro i k
    induction k with
    | zero => exact ‚ü®id, strictMono_id, rfl‚ü©
    | succ j ih =>
      obtain ‚ü®Ōą, hŌą_mono, hŌą_eq‚ü© := ih
      obtain ‚ü®Ōą', hŌą'_mono, hŌą'_eq‚ü© := hő¶_factor (i + j)
      refine ‚ü®Ōą ‚ąė Ōą', hŌą_mono.comp hŌą'_mono, ?_‚ü©
      show ő¶ (i + (j + 1)) = ő¶ i ‚ąė (Ōą ‚ąė Ōą')
      have heq : i + (j + 1) = (i + j) + 1 := by ring
      rw [heq, hŌą'_eq, ‚Üź Function.comp_assoc, ‚Üź hŌą_eq]
  -- Diagonal.
  let nsub : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē := fun k => ő¶ k k
  -- Strict monotonicity.
  have hnsub_mono : StrictMono nsub := by
    intro a b hab
    show ő¶ a a < ő¶ b b
    obtain ‚ü®Ōą, hŌą_mono, hŌą_eq‚ü© := hő¶_chain a (b - a)
    have heq : a + (b - a) = b := Nat.add_sub_of_le (le_of_lt hab)
    rw [heq] at hŌą_eq
    rw [hŌą_eq]
    show ő¶ a a < ő¶ a (Ōą b)
    apply hő¶_mono a
    have hŌą_ge : b ‚Č§ Ōą b := hŌą_mono.id_le b
    exact lt_of_lt_of_le hab hŌą_ge
  refine ‚ü®nsub, hnsub_mono, L, ?_‚ü©
  intro i
  -- Convergence at row i: tail of nsub (from index ‚Č• i) is a strictMono
  -- reindexing of ő¶ i.  Build őľ : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē so that nsub (i + j) = ő¶ i (őľ j)
  -- with őľ strictMono, then conclude via Tendsto.comp.
  -- Concretely: for each j, hő¶_chain i j gives Ōą_j strictMono with
  -- ő¶ (i + j) = ő¶ i ‚ąė Ōą_j, so nsub (i + j) = ő¶ i (Ōą_j (i + j)).
  -- Set őľ j := Ōą_j (i + j) and prove őľ strictMono.
  -- The Ōą_j's here are chosen via `Classical.choose`; since hő¶_chain's output
  -- is pulled from a specific term, consistency across j requires care.
  -- Cleaner: use the concrete `Ōą : ‚Ąē ‚Üí (‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē)` built into the recursion.
  --
  -- Define Ōą i (j) := the "increment extractor" at stage (i + j ‚Üí i + j + 1).
  let Ōąinc : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē := fun j =>
    (bwPick (fun k => s (j + 1) (ő¶ j k))
      (by obtain ‚ü®M, hM‚ü© := hs (j + 1); exact ‚ü®M, fun n => hM (ő¶ j n)‚ü©)).val.1
  -- By construction, ő¶ (j + 1) = ő¶ j ‚ąė Ōąinc j.
  have hŌąinc_mono : ‚ąÄ j, StrictMono (Ōąinc j) := fun j =>
    (bwPick (fun k => s (j + 1) (ő¶ j k))
      (by obtain ‚ü®M, hM‚ü© := hs (j + 1); exact ‚ü®M, fun n => hM (ő¶ j n)‚ü©)).property.1
  have hő¶_succ_eq : ‚ąÄ j, ő¶ (j + 1) = ő¶ j ‚ąė Ōąinc j := fun _ => rfl
  -- őł i j : the composition of Ōąinc i, Ōąinc (i+1), ..., Ōąinc (i+j-1).
  let őł : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē := fun j => Nat.rec (id : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē)
    (fun k prev => prev ‚ąė Ōąinc (i + k)) j
  have hőł_mono : ‚ąÄ j, StrictMono (őł j) := by
    intro j
    induction j with
    | zero => exact strictMono_id
    | succ k ih => exact ih.comp (hŌąinc_mono (i + k))
  have hő¶_ij_eq : ‚ąÄ j, ő¶ (i + j) = ő¶ i ‚ąė őł j := by
    intro j
    induction j with
    | zero => show ő¶ (i + 0) = ő¶ i ‚ąė id; simp
    | succ k ih =>
      show ő¶ (i + (k + 1)) = ő¶ i ‚ąė (őł k ‚ąė Ōąinc (i + k))
      have heq : i + (k + 1) = (i + k) + 1 := by ring
      rw [heq, hő¶_succ_eq (i + k), ‚Üź Function.comp_assoc, ‚Üź ih]
  -- őľ j := őł j (i + j).  Then nsub (i + j) = ő¶ i (őľ j), and őľ is strictMono.
  let őľ : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē := fun j => őł j (i + j)
  have hőł_succ_apply : ‚ąÄ k x, őł (k + 1) x = őł k (Ōąinc (i + k) x) := fun _ _ => rfl
  have hőľ_mono : StrictMono őľ := by
    apply strictMono_nat_of_lt_succ
    intro k
    show őł k (i + k) < őł (k + 1) (i + (k + 1))
    rw [hőł_succ_apply k (i + (k + 1))]
    apply hőł_mono k
    -- Need i + k < Ōąinc (i + k) (i + (k + 1))
    have hŌą_ge : i + (k + 1) ‚Č§ Ōąinc (i + k) (i + (k + 1)) :=
      (hŌąinc_mono (i + k)).id_le _
    exact lt_of_lt_of_le (Nat.lt_add_one (i + k) |>.trans_le (le_refl _)) hŌą_ge
  -- nsub (i + j) = ő¶ i (őľ j): follows from ő¶ (i + j) = ő¶ i ‚ąė őł j.
  have hnsub_eq : ‚ąÄ j, nsub (i + j) = ő¶ i (őľ j) := fun j =>
    congrArg (¬∑ (i + j)) (hő¶_ij_eq j)
  -- Stage-i convergence.
  have hő¶i_tendsto : Filter.Tendsto (fun k => s i (ő¶ i k)) Filter.atTop (nhds (L i)) := by
    cases i with
    | zero => exact hő¶0_tendsto
    | succ j => exact hő¶succ_tendsto j
  -- `fun j => s i (nsub (i + j)) = fun j => s i (ő¶ i (őľ j))` converges to L i.
  have hShifted : Filter.Tendsto (fun j => s i (nsub (i + j))) Filter.atTop (nhds (L i)) := by
    have h_eq : (fun j => s i (nsub (i + j))) = (fun k => s i (ő¶ i k)) ‚ąė őľ := by
      funext j; exact congrArg (s i) (hnsub_eq j)
    rw [h_eq]
    exact hő¶i_tendsto.comp hőľ_mono.tendsto_atTop
  -- Shift back via `tendsto_add_atTop_iff_nat`: `(fun j => f (i + j)) ‚Üí L ‚ÜĒ f ‚Üí L`.
  have h_eq_shift : (fun j : ‚Ąē => s i (nsub (i + j))) =
      (fun k : ‚Ąē => s i (nsub k)) ‚ąė (¬∑ + i) := by
    funext j; show s i (nsub (i + j)) = s i (nsub (j + i))
    rw [Nat.add_comm]
  rw [h_eq_shift] at hShifted
  exact (Filter.tendsto_add_atTop_iff_nat i).mp hShifted

/-! ### ¬ß10.165.C Rational-time subsequence for `HasModeLipschitzFamily`

Apply ¬ß10.165.B to the countable family `(m, q) ‚Ü¶ lip.modeCoeff ¬∑ q m`
indexed by `(Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) √ó ‚Ąö` via `Encodable`.  Time is clipped to
`max 0 q` to preserve row boundedness (the `modeBound` bound only holds
for `t ‚Č• 0`).  At each `q ‚Č• 0` with `q` rational, `max 0 q = q`, so the
extracted subsequence converges at every such `(m, q)`. -/

/-- **¬ß10.165.C  Rational-time subsequence.**  Given
`HasModeLipschitzFamily őĪ`, produce a strictly-monotone `nsub : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē`
and a limit `b_rat : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąö ‚Üí ‚Ąā` such that
`lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) (q : ‚ĄĚ) m ‚Üí b_rat m q` for every mode `m` and
every non-negative rational `q`. -/
theorem exists_rationalSubseq_tendsto
    {őĪ : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (‚Ü•(sqgBox n) ‚Üí ‚Ąā)}
    (lip : HasModeLipschitzFamily őĪ) :
    ‚ąÉ nsub : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē, StrictMono nsub ‚ąß
      ‚ąÉ b_rat : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąö ‚Üí ‚Ąā, ‚ąÄ (m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) (q : ‚Ąö), 0 ‚Č§ q ‚Üí
        Filter.Tendsto
          (fun k : ‚Ąē => lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) (q : ‚ĄĚ) m)
          Filter.atTop (nhds (b_rat m q)) := by
  classical
  -- Decode index k : ‚Ąē as pair (m, q) : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) √ó ‚Ąö via Encodable.
  let decodePair : ‚Ąē ‚Üí (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) √ó ‚Ąö := fun k =>
    (Encodable.decode (őĪ := (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) √ó ‚Ąö) k).getD ((fun _ => (0 : ‚Ą§)), 0)
  -- Clip the rational time to max 0 to ensure row boundedness.
  let s : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąā := fun k n =>
    lip.modeCoeff n (max 0 ((decodePair k).2 : ‚ĄĚ)) (decodePair k).1
  have hs : ‚ąÄ k : ‚Ąē, ‚ąÉ M : ‚ĄĚ, ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, ‚ÄĖs k n‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ M := fun k =>
    ‚ü®lip.modeBound (max 0 ((decodePair k).2 : ‚ĄĚ)),
     fun n => lip.modeBound_holds n _ _ (le_max_left _ _)‚ü©
  obtain ‚ü®nsub, hmono, L, hL‚ü© := cantor_diagonal_complex s hs
  refine ‚ü®nsub, hmono, fun m q => L (Encodable.encode (m, q)), ?_‚ü©
  intro m q hq
  have hdec : decodePair (Encodable.encode (m, q)) = (m, q) := by
    show (Encodable.decode (őĪ := (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) √ó ‚Ąö)
            (Encodable.encode (m, q))).getD _ = (m, q)
    rw [Encodable.encodek]
    rfl
  have hq_cast : (0 : ‚ĄĚ) ‚Č§ (q : ‚ĄĚ) := by exact_mod_cast hq
  have h_rw : ‚ąÄ n, s (Encodable.encode (m, q)) n = lip.modeCoeff n (q : ‚ĄĚ) m := by
    intro n
    show lip.modeCoeff n
          (max 0 ((decodePair (Encodable.encode (m, q))).2 : ‚ĄĚ))
          (decodePair (Encodable.encode (m, q))).1
        = lip.modeCoeff n (q : ‚ĄĚ) m
    rw [hdec]
    show lip.modeCoeff n (max 0 ((q : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ)) m = lip.modeCoeff n (q : ‚ĄĚ) m
    rw [max_eq_right hq_cast]
  have h_fn : (fun k : ‚Ąē => s (Encodable.encode (m, q)) (nsub k)) =
      fun k => lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) (q : ‚ĄĚ) m := by
    funext k; exact h_rw (nsub k)
  have := hL (Encodable.encode (m, q))
  rw [h_fn] at this
  exact this

/-! ### ¬ß10.165.D Extension of convergence from rational to real times

The rational-time subsequence of ¬ß10.165.C extends to every real time
`t ‚Č• 0` via the uniform Lipschitz-in-time bound of
`HasModeLipschitzFamily`.  The key argument is a standard three-term
bound: for any `t ‚Č• 0`, pick a rational `q ‚Č• 0` close to `t`; then
`|lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) t m - lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m|`
  `‚Č§ L|t - q| + |lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) q m - lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) q m| + L|q - t|`
with the middle term Cauchy (by rational convergence) and the outer two
small by rational approximation.  So the sequence is Cauchy in `‚Ąā`,
hence converges. -/

/-- **¬ß10.165.D  Convergence at real `t ‚Č• 0` from rational convergence.**
Given the rational-time subseq from ¬ß10.165.C and the uniform Lipschitz
bound of `HasModeLipschitzFamily`, extend the limit to every real
`t ‚Č• 0`. -/
theorem exists_realLimit_of_rationalSubseq
    {őĪ : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (‚Ü•(sqgBox n) ‚Üí ‚Ąā)}
    (lip : HasModeLipschitzFamily őĪ)
    {nsub : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē} (_hmono : StrictMono nsub)
    {b_rat : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąö ‚Üí ‚Ąā}
    (hRat : ‚ąÄ (m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) (q : ‚Ąö), 0 ‚Č§ q ‚Üí
      Filter.Tendsto
        (fun k : ‚Ąē => lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) (q : ‚ĄĚ) m)
        Filter.atTop (nhds (b_rat m q))) :
    ‚ąÉ b : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ‚Ąā, ‚ąÄ (m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) (t : ‚ĄĚ), 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
      Filter.Tendsto
        (fun k : ‚Ąē => lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m)
        Filter.atTop (nhds (b m t)) := by
  classical
  -- For each (m, t) with t ‚Č• 0, show the sequence is Cauchy.
  have hCauchy : ‚ąÄ (m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) (t : ‚ĄĚ), 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
      CauchySeq (fun k : ‚Ąē => lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m) := by
    intro m t ht
    rw [Metric.cauchySeq_iff]
    intro őĶ hőĶ
    set L := lip.modeLipschitz m with hLdef
    have hL_nn : 0 ‚Č§ L := lip.modeLipschitz_nonneg m
    -- Pick a rational q ‚Č• 0 close to t (distance < őĶ / (4 * (L + 1))).
    have h4L_pos : 0 < 4 * (L + 1) := by positivity
    have h_őĶ_over : 0 < őĶ / (4 * (L + 1)) := div_pos hőĶ h4L_pos
    -- ‚Ąö is dense in ‚ĄĚ: find q ‚ąą ‚Ąö with |t - q| < őĶ / (4L+4).
    obtain ‚ü®q, hq_close‚ü© :
        ‚ąÉ q : ‚Ąö, |t - (q : ‚ĄĚ)| < őĶ / (4 * (L + 1)) := by
      obtain ‚ü®q, hq1, hq2‚ü© :=
        exists_rat_btwn (sub_lt_self t h_őĶ_over : t - őĶ / (4 * (L + 1)) < t)
      refine ‚ü®q, ?_‚ü©
      rw [abs_sub_lt_iff]
      -- hq1 : t - őĶ/(4L+4) < q, hq2 : q < t
      -- Want: t - q < őĶ/(4L+4) and -(t - q) < őĶ/(4L+4)
      -- i.e., q < t + őĶ/(4L+4) (from hq2 as q < t < t + őĶ/(4L+4))
      -- and q > t - őĶ/(4L+4)  (from hq1)
      refine ‚ü®?_, ?_‚ü©
      ¬∑ -- t - q < őĶ/(4L+4): from hq1
        linarith
      ¬∑ -- (q : ‚ĄĚ) - t < őĶ/(4L+4): from hq2 we have q < t, so q - t < 0 < őĶ/(4L+4)
        linarith
    -- Clip q to non-negative.
    set q' : ‚Ąö := max 0 q with hq'_def
    have hq'_nn : 0 ‚Č§ q' := le_max_left _ _
    have hq'_close : |t - (q' : ‚ĄĚ)| < őĶ / (4 * (L + 1)) := by
      by_cases hq_sign : 0 ‚Č§ q
      ¬∑ -- q' = q
        have : q' = q := max_eq_right hq_sign
        rw [this]
        exact hq_close
      ¬∑ -- q' = 0, so |t - 0| = t.  We have q < 0 ‚Č§ t, so t < t - q < őĶ/(4L+4) via |t - q| < _.
        have hq_neg : q < 0 := lt_of_not_ge hq_sign
        have h0 : q' = 0 := max_eq_left (le_of_lt hq_neg)
        rw [h0]
        show |t - (0 : ‚Ąö)| < őĶ / (4 * (L + 1))
        have : ((0 : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) = 0 := by norm_cast
        rw [this, sub_zero]
        have ht_abs : |t| = t := abs_of_nonneg ht
        rw [ht_abs]
        -- Now t < őĶ/(4L+4).  From |t - q| < őĶ/(4L+4) and q < 0:
        -- t - q < őĶ/(4L+4) (from |t - q| < _, and t ‚Č• 0 > q means t - q ‚Č• 0)
        -- Since q < 0, -q > 0, so t < t + (-q) = t - q < őĶ/(4L+4).
        have h_tq : t - (q : ‚ĄĚ) < őĶ / (4 * (L + 1)) := by
          have := hq_close
          rw [abs_sub_lt_iff] at this
          exact this.1
        have hq_real_neg : ((q : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) < 0 := by exact_mod_cast hq_neg
        linarith
    -- From hRat at (m, q'), sequence converges, hence Cauchy.
    have hRat_mq := hRat m q' hq'_nn
    rw [Metric.tendsto_atTop] at hRat_mq
    obtain ‚ü®N, hN‚ü© := hRat_mq (őĶ / 4) (by linarith)
    refine ‚ü®N, fun j hj k hk => ?_‚ü©
    -- Triangle inequality: split through q'.
    have h_triangle :
        dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) t m) (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m)
          ‚Č§ dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) t m)
              (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) m)
            + dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) m)
                (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) m)
            + dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) m)
                (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m) := by
      have := dist_triangle4 (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) t m)
        (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) m)
        (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) m)
        (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m)
      linarith
    -- Bound each piece.
    have hq'_cast : (0 : ‚ĄĚ) ‚Č§ ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) := by exact_mod_cast hq'_nn
    have h1 : dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) t m)
                (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) m)
              ‚Č§ L * |t - ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ)| := by
      rw [dist_eq_norm]
      exact lip.modeLipschitz_holds (nsub j) m _ _ hq'_cast ht
    have h3 : dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) m)
                (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m)
              ‚Č§ L * |((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) - t| := by
      rw [dist_eq_norm]
      exact lip.modeLipschitz_holds (nsub k) m _ _ ht hq'_cast
    have habs_sym : |((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) - t| = |t - ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ)| := by
      rw [abs_sub_comm]
    rw [habs_sym] at h3
    -- The middle term: convergence + triangle.
    have h2 : dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) m)
                (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) m) < őĶ / 2 := by
      have hj_dist := hN j hj
      have hk_dist := hN k hk
      calc dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) m)
                (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) m)
          ‚Č§ dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) m) (b_rat m q')
            + dist (b_rat m q') (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ) m) :=
            dist_triangle _ _ _
        _ < őĶ / 4 + őĶ / 4 := by
            have := hj_dist
            have := hk_dist
            rw [dist_comm _ (b_rat m q')] at hk_dist
            linarith
        _ = őĶ / 2 := by ring
    -- Combine.  Bound: L * |t - q'| < őĶ/4 via |t - q'| < őĶ/(4(L+1)) and L ‚Č§ L+1.
    have hL_bound : L * |t - ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ)| < őĶ / 4 := by
      have h_abs_nn : 0 ‚Č§ |t - ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ)| := abs_nonneg _
      have hL1_pos : (0 : ‚ĄĚ) < L + 1 := by linarith
      have step1 : L * |t - ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ)| ‚Č§ (L + 1) * |t - ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ)| :=
        mul_le_mul_of_nonneg_right (by linarith) h_abs_nn
      have step2 : (L + 1) * |t - ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ)| < (L + 1) * (őĶ / (4 * (L + 1))) :=
        mul_lt_mul_of_pos_left hq'_close hL1_pos
      have step3 : (L + 1) * (őĶ / (4 * (L + 1))) = őĶ / 4 := by
        field_simp
      linarith
    calc dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) t m) (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m)
        ‚Č§ _ := h_triangle
      _ ‚Č§ L * |t - ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ)| + őĶ / 2 + L * |t - ((q' : ‚Ąö) : ‚ĄĚ)| := by linarith
      _ < őĶ / 4 + őĶ / 2 + őĶ / 4 := by linarith
      _ = őĶ := by ring
  -- Define b m t := limit of the Cauchy sequence.
  choose b hb using fun (m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) (t : ‚ĄĚ) (ht : 0 ‚Č§ t) =>
    cauchySeq_tendsto_of_complete (hCauchy m t ht)
  refine ‚ü®fun m t => if h : 0 ‚Č§ t then b m t h else 0, ?_‚ü©
  intro m t ht
  simp only [dif_pos ht]
  exact hb m t ht

/-! ### ¬ß10.165 `hExtract` witness -/

/-- **¬ß10.165  `hExtract` witness for ¬ß10.155.B.**  Given
`HasModeLipschitzFamily őĪ`, produce the classical Arzel√†‚ÄďAscoli +
Cantor diagonal extraction witness demanded by ¬ß10.155.B: a
strictly-monotone `nsub : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē` with per-mode pointwise convergence
at every `t ‚Č• 0`. -/
theorem sqgGalerkin_hExtract_witness
    {őĪ : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (‚Ü•(sqgBox n) ‚Üí ‚Ąā)}
    (lip : HasModeLipschitzFamily őĪ) :
    ‚ąÉ (nsub : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē), StrictMono nsub ‚ąß
      ‚ąÉ b : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ‚Ąā,
        ‚ąÄ (m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) (t : ‚ĄĚ), 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
          Filter.Tendsto
            (fun k : ‚Ąē =>
              galerkinExtend (sqgBox (nsub k)) (őĪ (nsub k) t) m)
            Filter.atTop (nhds (b m t)) := by
  obtain ‚ü®nsub, hmono, b_rat, hRat‚ü© := exists_rationalSubseq_tendsto lip
  obtain ‚ü®b, hb‚ü© := exists_realLimit_of_rationalSubseq lip hmono hRat
  refine ‚ü®nsub, hmono, b, ?_‚ü©
  intro m t ht
  -- Bridge via ¬ß10.155.A: lip.modeCoeff = galerkinExtend.
  have h_eq : ‚ąÄ k,
      galerkinExtend (sqgBox (nsub k)) (őĪ (nsub k) t) m = lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m :=
    fun k => (HasModeLipschitzFamily.modeCoeff_eq_galerkinExtend lip (nsub k) t m).symm
  have h_fn : (fun k : ‚Ąē => galerkinExtend (sqgBox (nsub k)) (őĪ (nsub k) t) m) =
      fun k => lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m := by
    funext k; exact h_eq k
  rw [h_fn]
  exact hb m t ht

/-! ### ¬ß10.166 Per-mode discharges of ¬ß10.153.C's `hDeriv` / `hCont`

¬ß10.166 extracts ¬ß10.153.C's restricted `hDeriv` and `hCont` hypotheses
from the whole-trajectory derivative produced by ¬ß10.116.  The
projection to coordinate `‚ü®m, hm‚ü© : ‚Ü•(sqgBox n)` uses mathlib's
`hasDerivWithinAt_pi` and `continuousOn_pi`.

The definitional identity
`galerkinVectorField (sqgBox n) c ‚ü®m, hm‚ü©
  = galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) c) m`
(line 13737 `rfl`) bridges the whole-vector-field form to the
`galerkinRHS`-against-`galerkinExtend` form ¬ß10.153.C expects.

With these discharges, ¬ß10.153.C's hypotheses are entirely consumable
from a ¬ß10.116 trajectory at every `m ‚ąą sqgBox n`; leakage modes
(handled internally by ¬ß10.153.C, see line 19920ff) need no extra data. -/

/-- **¬ß10.166.A  `hDeriv` discharge.**  Given the whole-trajectory
derivative of ¬ß10.116, project to the per-mode form ¬ß10.153.C demands:
for each `m ‚ąą sqgBox n` and each `ŌĄ ‚Č• 0`,
`ŌÉ ‚Ü¶ galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (őĪ n ŌÉ) m` has derivative
`galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (őĪ n ŌĄ)) m` at `ŌĄ`
on `Set.Ici ŌĄ`. -/
theorem sqgGalerkin_hDeriv_of_galerkinVectorField
    [DecidableEq (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)]
    (őĪ : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (‚Ü•(sqgBox n) ‚Üí ‚Ąā))
    (hőĪ : ‚ąÄ (n : ‚Ąē) (ŌĄ : ‚ĄĚ), 0 ‚Č§ ŌĄ ‚Üí
      HasDerivWithinAt (őĪ n) (galerkinVectorField (sqgBox n) (őĪ n ŌĄ))
        (Set.Ici (0 : ‚ĄĚ)) ŌĄ)
    (n : ‚Ąē) (ŌĄ : ‚ĄĚ) (hŌĄ : 0 ‚Č§ ŌĄ) (m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) (hm : m ‚ąą sqgBox n) :
    HasDerivWithinAt (fun ŌÉ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (őĪ n ŌÉ) m)
      (galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (őĪ n ŌĄ)) m)
      (Set.Ici ŌĄ) ŌĄ := by
  have h_pi := hasDerivWithinAt_pi.mp (hőĪ n ŌĄ hŌĄ) ‚ü®m, hm‚ü©
  have h_fn : (fun ŌÉ => őĪ n ŌÉ ‚ü®m, hm‚ü©) = fun ŌÉ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (őĪ n ŌÉ) m := by
    funext ŌÉ; exact (galerkinExtend_apply_of_mem _ _ hm).symm
  have h_vf : galerkinVectorField (sqgBox n) (őĪ n ŌĄ) ‚ü®m, hm‚ü©
      = galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (őĪ n ŌĄ)) m := rfl
  rw [h_fn, h_vf] at h_pi
  exact h_pi.mono (Set.Ici_subset_Ici.mpr hŌĄ)

/-- **¬ß10.166.B  `hCont` discharge.**  Given the whole-trajectory
derivative of ¬ß10.116 (which gives continuity on `Ici 0`), project and
restrict to obtain the `ContinuousOn ... (Icc s t)` form ¬ß10.153.C
demands. -/
theorem sqgGalerkin_hCont_of_galerkinVectorField
    [DecidableEq (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)]
    (őĪ : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (‚Ü•(sqgBox n) ‚Üí ‚Ąā))
    (hőĪ : ‚ąÄ (n : ‚Ąē) (ŌĄ : ‚ĄĚ), 0 ‚Č§ ŌĄ ‚Üí
      HasDerivWithinAt (őĪ n) (galerkinVectorField (sqgBox n) (őĪ n ŌĄ))
        (Set.Ici (0 : ‚ĄĚ)) ŌĄ)
    (n : ‚Ąē) (m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) (hm : m ‚ąą sqgBox n) (s t : ‚ĄĚ) (hs : 0 ‚Č§ s) (hst : s ‚Č§ t) :
    ContinuousOn (fun ŌÉ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (őĪ n ŌÉ) m) (Set.Icc s t) := by
  have hőĪ_cont : ContinuousOn (őĪ n) (Set.Ici (0 : ‚ĄĚ)) := fun ŌĄ hŌĄ =>
    (hőĪ n ŌĄ hŌĄ).continuousWithinAt
  have h_coord : ContinuousOn (fun ŌÉ => őĪ n ŌÉ ‚ü®m, hm‚ü©) (Set.Ici (0 : ‚ĄĚ)) :=
    continuousOn_pi.mp hőĪ_cont ‚ü®m, hm‚ü©
  have h_fn : (fun ŌÉ => őĪ n ŌÉ ‚ü®m, hm‚ü©) = fun ŌÉ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (őĪ n ŌÉ) m := by
    funext ŌÉ; exact (galerkinExtend_apply_of_mem _ _ hm).symm
  rw [h_fn] at h_coord
  exact h_coord.mono (fun x hx => le_trans hs hx.1)

/-! ### ¬ß10.167 `MaterialMaxPrinciple` off the finite-Fourier-support class

Item 3 of `OPEN.md`.  Extends ¬ß10.56's MMP discharge ‚ÄĒ which only
applied to trajectories with **fixed finite** Fourier support and a
uniform coefficient bound ‚ÄĒ to the `L¬≤`-limit class:  given a Galerkin
sequence converging strongly in `L¬≤` pointwise in time to a limit `őł`
and a **uniform-in-`n`-and-`t`** `ŠłĘ¬Ļ` bound on the Galerkin states,
`MaterialMaxPrinciple őł` holds.

The route is the classical one:  lower-semicontinuity of the `ŠłĘ¬Ļ`
seminorm under strong-`L¬≤` convergence.  Since each Fourier
coefficient is a continuous linear functional of `f ‚ąą L¬≤`, per-mode
convergence `fŐā‚āô(m) ‚Üí fŐā(m)` follows from strong-`L¬≤` convergence
(¬ß10.141).  Finite-Fourier partial sums then pass to the limit
continuously, and an `iSup`-bounded family of partial sums is summable
with tsum ‚Č§ the uniform bound.

This extension closes Item 3 without introducing any analytic axiom:
the uniform `ŠłĘ¬Ļ` bound becomes an explicit hypothesis of the consumer,
which is exactly what classical regularity theory supplies at the
level of Galerkin approximation.

### ¬ß10.167.A Lower-semicontinuity of `hsSeminormSq` under `L¬≤` limits

Structural lemma.  Given an `L¬≤`-convergent sequence `f‚āô ‚Üí g` with a
uniform bound on `hsSeminormSq s (f‚āô)`, the limit `g` satisfies the
same bound, and its weighted Fourier-coefficient family is summable. -/

/-- **¬ß10.167.A  Lower-semicontinuity of `hsSeminormSq s` under strong-
`L¬≤` convergence.**

If `f‚āô ‚Üí g` strongly in `L¬≤` and `hsSeminormSq s (f‚āô) ‚Č§ M` uniformly in
`n`, with each `f‚āô`'s weighted Fourier-coefficient family summable,
then the weighted family for `g` is summable and `hsSeminormSq s g ‚Č§ M`.

Proof.  Per-mode convergence `mFourierCoeff f‚āô m ‚Üí mFourierCoeff g m`
(¬ß10.141) lifts to `(fracDerivSymbol s m)¬≤ ¬∑ ‚ÄĖ¬∑‚ÄĖ¬≤` via continuity of
squaring and multiplication.  Finite sums `‚ąĎ m ‚ąą F, weighted g m` are
limits of `‚ąĎ m ‚ąą F, weighted f‚āô m`, each bounded by `hsSeminormSq s f‚āô ‚Č§ M`
via `Summable.sum_le_tsum`.  Therefore every finset sum of the `g`-family
is bounded by `M`, and `summable_of_sum_le` / `Real.tsum_le_of_sum_le`
conclude. -/
theorem hsSeminormSq_le_of_L2_limit_uniform_bound
    {d : Type*} [Fintype d]
    (s : ‚ĄĚ) {M : ‚ĄĚ}
    {f‚āô : ‚Ąē ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus d))}
    {g : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus d))}
    (hConv : Filter.Tendsto (fun n => ‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖf‚āô n x - g x‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
      Filter.atTop (nhds 0))
    (hSumm_fn : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, Summable (fun m : d ‚Üí ‚Ą§ =>
      (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (f‚āô n) m‚ÄĖ ^ 2))
    (hBound : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, hsSeminormSq s (f‚āô n) ‚Č§ M) :
    Summable (fun m : d ‚Üí ‚Ą§ =>
        (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff g m‚ÄĖ ^ 2) ‚ąß
      hsSeminormSq s g ‚Č§ M := by
  -- Per-mode Fourier coefficient convergence (¬ß10.141).
  have h_coeff_conv : ‚ąÄ m : d ‚Üí ‚Ą§,
      Filter.Tendsto (fun n => mFourierCoeff (f‚āô n) m)
        Filter.atTop (nhds (mFourierCoeff g m)) :=
    fun m => tendsto_mFourierCoeff_of_tendsto_L2Sq hConv m
  -- Lift to squared norms and then weighted terms.
  have h_weighted_conv : ‚ąÄ m : d ‚Üí ‚Ą§,
      Filter.Tendsto
        (fun n => (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (f‚āô n) m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
        Filter.atTop
        (nhds ((fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff g m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)) := by
    intro m
    have h_norm : Filter.Tendsto (fun n => ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (f‚āô n) m‚ÄĖ)
        Filter.atTop (nhds ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff g m‚ÄĖ) := (h_coeff_conv m).norm
    have h_sq : Filter.Tendsto (fun n => ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (f‚āô n) m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
        Filter.atTop (nhds (‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff g m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)) := h_norm.pow 2
    exact h_sq.const_mul _
  -- For every finite `F`, the partial sum for `g` is bounded by `M`.
  have h_nonneg : ‚ąÄ m : d ‚Üí ‚Ą§,
      0 ‚Č§ (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff g m‚ÄĖ ^ 2 :=
    fun m => mul_nonneg (sq_nonneg _) (sq_nonneg _)
  have h_nonneg_fn : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, ‚ąÄ m : d ‚Üí ‚Ą§,
      0 ‚Č§ (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (f‚āô n) m‚ÄĖ ^ 2 :=
    fun _ m => mul_nonneg (sq_nonneg _) (sq_nonneg _)
  have h_finset_bound : ‚ąÄ F : Finset (d ‚Üí ‚Ą§),
      ‚ąĎ m ‚ąą F, (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff g m‚ÄĖ ^ 2 ‚Č§ M := by
    intro F
    -- Partial sum continuity via `tendsto_finset_sum`.
    have h_fin_conv : Filter.Tendsto
        (fun n => ‚ąĎ m ‚ąą F, (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (f‚āô n) m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
        Filter.atTop
        (nhds (‚ąĎ m ‚ąą F, (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff g m‚ÄĖ ^ 2)) :=
      tendsto_finset_sum F (fun m _ => h_weighted_conv m)
    -- Each partial sum along the sequence is bounded by `M`.
    have h_fin_le : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē,
        ‚ąĎ m ‚ąą F, (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (f‚āô n) m‚ÄĖ ^ 2 ‚Č§ M := by
      intro n
      calc ‚ąĎ m ‚ąą F, (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (f‚āô n) m‚ÄĖ ^ 2
          ‚Č§ ‚ąĎ' m : d ‚Üí ‚Ą§,
              (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (f‚āô n) m‚ÄĖ ^ 2 :=
            (hSumm_fn n).sum_le_tsum F (fun m _ => h_nonneg_fn n m)
        _ = hsSeminormSq s (f‚āô n) := rfl
        _ ‚Č§ M := hBound n
    exact le_of_tendsto' h_fin_conv h_fin_le
  refine ‚ü®summable_of_sum_le (fun m => h_nonneg m) h_finset_bound, ?_‚ü©
  exact Real.tsum_le_of_sum_le (fun m => h_nonneg m) h_finset_bound

/-! ### ¬ß10.167.B `MaterialMaxPrinciple` from `L¬≤`-limit + uniform `ŠłĘ¬Ļ`

Extends ¬ß10.56 to the `L¬≤`-limit class.  Given a time-varying `őł` that
is the pointwise-in-`t` `L¬≤` limit of a sequence `f‚āô` of time-varying
`L¬≤` functions, each satisfying a uniform `ŠłĘ¬Ļ` bound and summability,
`MaterialMaxPrinciple őł` holds with bound `M`. -/

/-- **¬ß10.167.B  MMP discharge from an `L¬≤`-limit sequence with uniform
`ŠłĘ¬Ļ` control.**

The hypotheses are the minimum needed for MMP to propagate under
strong-`L¬≤` convergence:

* `hConv` ‚ÄĒ pointwise-in-`t` strong-`L¬≤` convergence `f‚āô(t) ‚Üí őł(t)`.
* `hSumm_fn` ‚ÄĒ per-`n`-per-`t` summability of the `ŠłĘ¬Ļ` weighted
  Fourier family on `f‚āô`.
* `hBound` ‚ÄĒ uniform-in-`n`-and-`t` `ŠłĘ¬Ļ` bound on `f‚āô`.

Produces `MaterialMaxPrinciple őł` via ¬ß10.167.A at every forward
time. -/
theorem MaterialMaxPrinciple.of_L2_limit_uniform_H1
    (őł : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (f‚āô : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (hConv : ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
      Filter.Tendsto (fun n => ‚ąę x, ‚ÄĖf‚āô n t x - őł t x‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
        Filter.atTop (nhds 0))
    (M : ‚ĄĚ)
    (hSumm_fn : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
      Summable (fun m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ =>
        (fracDerivSymbol 1 m) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (f‚āô n t) m‚ÄĖ ^ 2))
    (hBound : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí hsSeminormSq 1 (f‚āô n t) ‚Č§ M) :
    MaterialMaxPrinciple őł where
  hOnePropagation := ‚ü®M, fun t ht =>
    (hsSeminormSq_le_of_L2_limit_uniform_bound (s := 1) (M := M)
      (hConv t ht) (fun n => hSumm_fn n t ht) (fun n => hBound n t ht)).2‚ü©
  hOneSummability := fun t ht =>
    (hsSeminormSq_le_of_L2_limit_uniform_bound (s := 1) (M := M)
      (hConv t ht) (fun n => hSumm_fn n t ht) (fun n => hBound n t ht)).1
  freeDerivativeAtKappaMax := trivial
  materialSegmentExpansion := trivial
  farFieldBoundary := trivial

/-! ### ¬ß10.167.C `MaterialMaxPrinciple` for the Aubin‚ÄďLions limit

Specializes ¬ß10.167.B to the `HasAubinLionsExtraction` witness from
¬ß10.139.  Given a Galerkin family `őĪ` with finite-support states
`galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (őĪ n t)` and uniform-in-`n`-and-`t` `ŠłĘ¬Ļ`
bound, the Aubin‚ÄďLions limit `ext.őł_lim` satisfies
`MaterialMaxPrinciple`.  Combined with ¬ß10.56's finite-support
discharge on each level, this delivers MMP for the infinite-support
limit from a single `ŠłĘ¬Ļ` bound hypothesis on the Galerkin
approximation. -/

/-- **Auxiliary: `galerkinToLp` has vanishing Fourier coefficients off
its support `S`.**  Direct consequence of `mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp`
and `galerkinExtend_apply_of_not_mem`.  Exposed separately to short-
circuit elaboration in ¬ß10.167.C (otherwise the `by rw [...]` body
triggers a deep `whnf` unfolding loop inside the `of_L2_limit` field
of the consumer). -/
theorem mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp_eq_zero_of_not_mem
    (S : Finset (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)) [DecidableEq (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)]
    (c : ‚Ü•S ‚Üí ‚Ąā) {m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§} (hm : m ‚ąČ S) :
    mFourierCoeff (galerkinToLp S c) m = 0 := by
  rw [mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp, galerkinExtend_apply_of_not_mem _ _ hm]

/-- **Auxiliary: weighted `ŠłĘ¬Ļ` Fourier family of a `galerkinToLp` state
is summable.**  Derives summability from `hsSeminormSq_summable_of_finite_support`
using the support witness above.  Packaged as a standalone lemma so
that ¬ß10.167.C is a plain term-level composition of named results. -/
theorem hsSeminormSq_one_summable_galerkinToLp
    (S : Finset (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)) [DecidableEq (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)]
    (c : ‚Ü•S ‚Üí ‚Ąā) :
    Summable (fun m : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ =>
      (fracDerivSymbol 1 m) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (galerkinToLp S c) m‚ÄĖ ^ 2) :=
  hsSeminormSq_summable_of_finite_support 1 (galerkinToLp S c) S
    (fun m hm => mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp_eq_zero_of_not_mem S c hm)

/-- **¬ß10.167.C  MMP discharge for the Aubin‚ÄďLions limit.**

Consumes a `HasAubinLionsExtraction` witness plus a uniform-in-`n`-and-
`t` `ŠłĘ¬Ļ` bound on the Galerkin states `galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (őĪ n t)`
and produces `MaterialMaxPrinciple (ext.őł_lim)` via ¬ß10.167.B.  The
pointwise-in-`t` strong-`L¬≤` convergence comes from `ext.tendsto_L2`.

No explicit `[DecidableEq (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)]` binder: the previous attempts
introduced one, which caused an instance-synthesis mismatch with
`ext.tendsto_L2` (whose `galerkinToLp` calls invoke the auto-synthesized
`Fintype.decidablePiFintype` instance).  Auto-synthesis is used
uniformly throughout this theorem so all `galerkinToLp` applications
agree on the DecidableEq instance. -/
theorem MaterialMaxPrinciple.of_aubinLions_uniform_H1
    {őł : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    {őĪ : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (‚Ü•(sqgBox n) ‚Üí ‚Ąā)}
    (ext : HasAubinLionsExtraction őł őĪ)
    (M : ‚ĄĚ)
    (hBound : ‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
      hsSeminormSq 1 (galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (őĪ n t)) ‚Č§ M) :
    MaterialMaxPrinciple ext.őł_lim := by
  refine MaterialMaxPrinciple.of_L2_limit_uniform_H1 (őł := ext.őł_lim)
    (f‚āô := fun k t => galerkinToLp (sqgBox (ext.nsub k)) (őĪ (ext.nsub k) t))
    ?_ M ?_ ?_
  ¬∑ intro t ht
    exact ext.tendsto_L2 t ht
  ¬∑ intro k t _
    exact hsSeminormSq_one_summable_galerkinToLp
      (sqgBox (ext.nsub k)) (őĪ (ext.nsub k) t)
  ¬∑ intro k t ht
    exact hBound (ext.nsub k) t ht

/-! ### ¬ß10.168 `BKMCriterionS2` off the finite-Fourier-support class

Item 4 of `OPEN.md`.  Parallel companion to ¬ß10.167: lifts ¬ß10.57
