`SqgEvolutionAxioms`) yields the strong axioms. This is the
closure of the model-correctness loop: the repo's final
conditional Theorem 3 now sits on a predicate that is ‚ÄĒ modulo the
absorbed density step ‚ÄĒ the textbook definition of an SQG weak
solution. -/
theorem SqgEvolutionAxioms_strong.of_testFormWeakSolution_via_MMP
    {őł : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    (hE : SqgEvolutionAxioms őł)
    (hMMP : MaterialMaxPrinciple őł)
    (u : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (hu_velocity : ‚ąÄ (j : Fin 2) (ŌĄ : ‚ĄĚ), IsSqgVelocityComponent (őł ŌĄ) (u j ŌĄ) j)
    (hW : IsSqgTestFormWeakSolution őł u) :
    SqgEvolutionAxioms_strong őł :=
  SqgEvolutionAxioms_strong.of_IsSqgWeakSolution_via_MMP
    hE hMMP u hu_velocity (IsSqgWeakSolution.of_testFormWeakSolution hW)

/-- **¬ß12 ‚ÄĒ Zero-datum witness of `IsSqgTestFormWeakSolution`.**

The identically-zero scalar field `őł ‚Č° 0` satisfies the classical
distributional weak form against every separated test
`ŌÜ = Ōą¬∑e_m`: both pairings vanish because `őł ‚Č° 0` and
`sqgNonlinearFlux 0 u m = 0` (¬ß10.16 `sqgNonlinearFlux_zero_theta`).
The collar limit is the zero function's constant Fourier
coefficients (¬ß10.17 `SqgFourierContinuous.zero`). Flux bound is
trivially `K = 0`. This ensures the new predicate and constructor
elaborate on a concrete model. -/
theorem IsSqgTestFormWeakSolution.zero
    (u : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))) :
    IsSqgTestFormWeakSolution
      (fun _ => (0 : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))) u := by
  refine
    { testForm := IsSqgWeakSolutionTimeTest.zero u
      collar := ?_
      fluxBound := ‚ü®0, le_refl 0, ?_‚ü©
      fluxMeas := ?_ }
  ¬∑ -- collar: on the zero field, every mFourierCoeff is the zero constant,
    -- so the LHS integral is identically 0 and its limit is
    -- 0 = mFourierCoeff 0 m - mFourierCoeff 0 m.
    intro m s t _ _
    have h_coef_zero : ‚ąÄ ŌĄ : ‚ĄĚ,
        mFourierCoeff
            ((fun _ : ‚ĄĚ =>
              (0 : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))) ŌĄ) m = 0 :=
      fun _ => mFourierCoeff_zero m
    have h_int : ‚ąÄ őĶ : ‚ĄĚ,
        ‚ąę ŌĄ, deriv (fun ŌĄ => (sqgConcreteMollifier őĶ s t ŌĄ : ‚Ąā)) ŌĄ
               * mFourierCoeff
                  ((fun _ : ‚ĄĚ =>
                    (0 : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))) ŌĄ) m
           = 0 := by
      intro őĶ
      have hfun : (fun ŌĄ : ‚ĄĚ =>
          deriv (fun ŌĄ => (sqgConcreteMollifier őĶ s t ŌĄ : ‚Ąā)) ŌĄ
            * mFourierCoeff
                ((fun _ : ‚ĄĚ =>
                  (0 : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))) ŌĄ) m)
            = fun _ => (0 : ‚Ąā) := by
        funext ŌĄ
        rw [h_coef_zero ŌĄ]
        ring
      rw [hfun, integral_zero]
    have h_target :
        mFourierCoeff
            ((fun _ : ‚ĄĚ =>
              (0 : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))) s) m
          - mFourierCoeff
              ((fun _ : ‚ĄĚ =>
                (0 : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))) t) m
          = (0 : ‚Ąā) := by
      simp [h_coef_zero]
    rw [h_target]
    -- The function is identically 0, so the Tendsto reduces to a constant-0 filter.
    have hfun_őĶ : (fun őĶ : ‚ĄĚ => ‚ąę ŌĄ,
            deriv (fun ŌĄ => (sqgConcreteMollifier őĶ s t ŌĄ : ‚Ąā)) ŌĄ
              * mFourierCoeff
                  ((fun _ : ‚ĄĚ =>
                    (0 : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))) ŌĄ) m)
          = fun _ : ‚ĄĚ => (0 : ‚Ąā) := by
      funext őĶ; exact h_int őĶ
    rw [hfun_őĶ]
    exact tendsto_const_nhds
  ¬∑ -- fluxBound: sqgNonlinearFlux of the zero field vanishes.
    intro m ŌĄ
    rw [sqgNonlinearFlux_zero_theta]
    simp
  ¬∑ -- fluxMeas: flux is identically 0 in ŌĄ, so measurable.
    intro m
    have hfun : (fun ŌĄ : ‚ĄĚ =>
        sqgNonlinearFlux
            ((fun _ : ‚ĄĚ =>
              (0 : Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))) ŌĄ)
            (fun j => u j ŌĄ) m)
          = fun _ => (0 : ‚Ąā) := by
      funext ŌĄ; exact sqgNonlinearFlux_zero_theta (fun j => u j ŌĄ) m
    rw [hfun]
    exact aestronglyMeasurable_const

/-! ## ¬ß13 Lattice Sobolev: per-mode `ŠłĘňĘ` sup bound

`(fracDerivSymbol őĪ m)¬≤ ¬∑ ‚ÄĖc m‚ÄĖ¬≤ ‚Č§ trigPolyEnergyHs s S c` for every `őĪ ‚Č§ s`
and every `m ‚ąą S`.  Direct consequence of (i) the definition of
`trigPolyEnergyHs` as a sum of non-negative terms, and (ii) monotonicity
`latticeNorm^őĪ ‚Č§ latticeNorm^s` at `latticeNorm ‚Č• 1` when `őĪ ‚Č§ s`.

Discrete analogue of the classical inequality `‚ÄĖu‚ÄĖ¬≤_{ŠłĘ^őĪ} ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖu‚ÄĖ¬≤_{ŠłĘňĘ}`
applied pointwise at each Fourier mode.  Closes the Sobolev-embedding
leg of Gap A on the lattice side.  Uniform in `S` (independent of the
Galerkin level `n` when `S = sqgBox n`). -/

set_option diagnostics true in
set_option diagnostics.threshold 100 in
/-- **¬ß13.1 ‚ÄĒ Monotone comparison of `fracDerivSymbol` in the exponent
at a nonzero mode.**  For `őĪ ‚Č§ s` and `m ‚Č† 0` in the lattice,
`fracDerivSymbol őĪ m ‚Č§ fracDerivSymbol s m`. -/
lemma fracDerivSymbol_mono_of_le_exp
    {d : Type*} [Fintype d] {őĪ s : ‚ĄĚ} (hőĪs : őĪ ‚Č§ s)
    {n : d ‚Üí ‚Ą§} (hn : n ‚Č† 0) :
    fracDerivSymbol őĪ n ‚Č§ fracDerivSymbol s n := by
  rw [fracDerivSymbol_of_ne_zero őĪ hn, fracDerivSymbol_of_ne_zero s hn]
  have hL : 1 ‚Č§ latticeNorm n := latticeNorm_ge_one_of_ne_zero hn
  exact Real.rpow_le_rpow_of_exponent_le hL hőĪs

set_option diagnostics true in
set_option diagnostics.threshold 100 in
/-- **¬ß13.2 ‚ÄĒ `fracDerivSymbol` squared, monotone in exponent.**  For
`0 ‚Č§ őĪ ‚Č§ s` and every `n`, `(fracDerivSymbol őĪ n)¬≤ ‚Č§ (fracDerivSymbol s n)¬≤`. -/
lemma fracDerivSymbol_sq_mono_exp
    {d : Type*} [Fintype d] {őĪ s : ‚ĄĚ} (hőĪ : 0 ‚Č§ őĪ) (hőĪs : őĪ ‚Č§ s)
    (n : d ‚Üí ‚Ą§) :
    (fracDerivSymbol őĪ n) ^ 2 ‚Č§ (fracDerivSymbol s n) ^ 2 := by
  by_cases hn : n = 0
  ¬∑ rw [hn, fracDerivSymbol_zero, fracDerivSymbol_zero]
  ¬∑ have h := fracDerivSymbol_mono_of_le_exp hőĪs hn
    have hőĪnn : 0 ‚Č§ fracDerivSymbol őĪ n := fracDerivSymbol_nonneg őĪ n
    exact pow_le_pow_left‚āÄ hőĪnn h 2

set_option diagnostics true in
set_option diagnostics.threshold 100 in
/-- **¬ß13.3 ‚ÄĒ Per-mode Sobolev embedding bound.**  For `0 ‚Č§ őĪ ‚Č§ s` and
every `m ‚ąą S`,
`(fracDerivSymbol őĪ m.val)¬≤ ¬∑ ‚ÄĖc m‚ÄĖ¬≤ ‚Č§ trigPolyEnergyHs s S c`.

Keystone of the lattice Sobolev sup bound: bounds every individual mode
contribution to `ŠłĘ^őĪ` by the total `ŠłĘňĘ` energy, uniformly in the mode
and uniformly in the ambient lattice `S`. -/
theorem fracDerivSymbol_sq_mul_norm_sq_le_trigPolyEnergyHs
    {őĪ s : ‚ĄĚ} (hőĪ : 0 ‚Č§ őĪ) (hőĪs : őĪ ‚Č§ s)
    {S : Finset (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)} [DecidableEq (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§)]
    (c : ‚Ü•S ‚Üí ‚Ąā) (m : ‚Ü•S) :
    (fracDerivSymbol őĪ m.val) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖc m‚ÄĖ ^ 2 ‚Č§ trigPolyEnergyHs s S c := by
  -- Step 1: bound LHS by (fracDerivSymbol s m.val)¬≤ ¬∑ ‚ÄĖc m‚ÄĖ¬≤ via ¬ß13.2.
  have hstep :
      (fracDerivSymbol őĪ m.val) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖc m‚ÄĖ ^ 2
        ‚Č§ (fracDerivSymbol s m.val) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖc m‚ÄĖ ^ 2 :=
    mul_le_mul_of_nonneg_right (fracDerivSymbol_sq_mono_exp hőĪ hőĪs m.val) (sq_nonneg _)
  refine hstep.trans ?_
  -- Step 2: isolate the single `m`-term of the energy sum and bound by the sum.
  unfold trigPolyEnergyHs
  refine Finset.single_le_sum
    (f := fun k : ‚Ü•S => (fracDerivSymbol s k.val) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖc k‚ÄĖ ^ 2)
    ?_ (Finset.mem_univ m)
  intro k _
  exact mul_nonneg (sq_nonneg _) (sq_nonneg _)

/-! ### ¬ßB.15 Inverse Fourier transform: `L¬≤` from summable Fourier coefficients

Given a square-summable sequence of Fourier coefficients
`c : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąā`, produce a unique `L¬≤` function whose
`mFourierCoeff` recovers `c`.  This is just the `HilbertBasis.repr.symm`
of the `mFourierBasis` applied to the packaged `‚Ąď¬≤` element.
-/

section LpFromFourier

open UnitAddTorus MeasureTheory

/-- The underlying `‚Ąď¬≤((Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§), ‚Ąā)` element built from a summable
coefficient sequence. -/
noncomputable def lpCoeff
    (c : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąā)
    (hSum : Summable (fun k => ‚ÄĖc k‚ÄĖ ^ 2)) :
    ‚Ąď¬≤((Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§), ‚Ąā) :=
  ‚ü®c, by
    -- `Mem‚Ąďp c 2` follows from `Summable (‚ÄĖc ¬∑‚ÄĖ ^ (2 : ‚ĄĚ))`.
    have h2 : (2 : ENNReal).toReal = 2 := by
      simp [ENNReal.toReal_ofNat]
    have hReal : Summable (fun k : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) => ‚ÄĖc k‚ÄĖ ^ (2 : ENNReal).toReal) := by
      have hcongr : (fun k : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) => ‚ÄĖc k‚ÄĖ ^ (2 : ENNReal).toReal)
                  = (fun k : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) => ‚ÄĖc k‚ÄĖ ^ 2) := by
        funext k
        rw [h2]
        exact Real.rpow_two _
      rw [hcongr]; exact hSum
    exact mem‚Ąďp_gen hReal‚ü©

@[simp] lemma lpCoeff_apply
    (c : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąā)
    (hSum : Summable (fun k => ‚ÄĖc k‚ÄĖ ^ 2)) (k : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) :
    (lpCoeff c hSum : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąā) k = c k := rfl

/-- Inverse Fourier transform: from summable Fourier coefficients on `ūĚēč¬≤`,
produce an `L¬≤` function with those coefficients. -/
noncomputable def lpOfFourierCoeff
    (c : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąā)
    (hSum : Summable (fun k => ‚ÄĖc k‚ÄĖ ^ 2)) :
    Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))) :=
  mFourierBasis.repr.symm (lpCoeff c hSum)

/-- The forward Fourier coefficient inverts `lpOfFourierCoeff`. -/
theorem mFourierCoeff_lpOfFourierCoeff
    (c : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąā)
    (hSum : Summable (fun k => ‚ÄĖc k‚ÄĖ ^ 2)) (k : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) :
    mFourierCoeff (lpOfFourierCoeff c hSum) k = c k := by
  -- `mFourierBasis.repr f k = mFourierCoeff f k` on `L¬≤(ūĚēč¬≤)`.
  have hrepr := mFourierBasis_repr (d := Fin 2) (lpOfFourierCoeff c hSum) k
  -- `repr (repr.symm x) = x`, so `repr (lpOfFourierCoeff c hSum) = lpCoeff c hSum`.
  have hround : mFourierBasis.repr (lpOfFourierCoeff c hSum) = lpCoeff c hSum := by
    unfold lpOfFourierCoeff
    exact LinearIsometryEquiv.apply_symm_apply _ _
  -- Read off the `k`-th component.
  have h1 : (mFourierBasis.repr (lpOfFourierCoeff c hSum) : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąā) k
        = (lpCoeff c hSum : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąā) k := by
    rw [hround]
  have h2 : (lpCoeff c hSum : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąā) k = c k := rfl
  -- Combine.
  calc mFourierCoeff (lpOfFourierCoeff c hSum) k
      = mFourierBasis.repr (lpOfFourierCoeff c hSum) k := hrepr.symm
    _ = (lpCoeff c hSum : (Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§) ‚Üí ‚Ąā) k := h1
    _ = c k := h2

end LpFromFourier

/-! ## ¬ß14 Conditional-regularity hypotheses ‚ÄĒ paper ¬ß9.6.3 + ¬ß9.8 naming

Paper `paper/sqg-identity.md` ¬ß9.6.3 names Theorem 3 (SQG regularity,
conditional) as conditional on two explicit hypotheses (H-strain) and
(H-bdry).  Paper ¬ß9.8 provides an alternative single-hypothesis
reformulation (H-őĪ) via the *thermostat ratio*
`őĪ(t) := S_source(t) / (4¬∑|nSn(x(t),t)|¬∑V(t))`, with Prop 9.11 asserting
`(H-őĪ) ‚áí (H-strain) + (H-bdry)`.

This section introduces the Lean-side named hypothesis bundles paralleling
each, so that downstream consumers can cite the paper's labels directly.
The three bundles are **intentionally abstract** at the present level of
the formalization: they name the conditional content of ¬ß9 and ¬ß9.8,
but the ¬ß9 analytical derivation `(H-strain) + (H-bdry) ‚áí uniform ŠłĘ¬Ļ
bound` (i.e. `MaterialMaxPrinciple.hOnePropagation`) is **not** discharged
in this repository ‚ÄĒ it is the classical content the paper develops and
is summarised as `MaterialMaxPrinciple.of_HstrainHbdry`'s signature, which
takes the uniform ŠłĘ¬Ļ bound as an additional input, documenting the
non-formalised classical step.

Zero-datum witnesses for each of (H-strain), (H-bdry), (H-őĪ) are provided
for minimal-sanity use downstream. -/

/-- **(H-strain) ‚ÄĒ Normal-strain lower bound along tracked curvature maxima.**

Paper ¬ß9.6.3, verbatim:
*"There exists `őľ‚čÜ = őľ‚čÜ(őł‚āÄ) > 0` such that, along the material segment
`ő©(t)` around `x‚čÜ(t)`, the normal strain at every interior curvature
maximum `s_max(t)` satisfies `|nSn(s_max(t), t)| ‚Č• őľ‚čÜ` for all `t ‚Č• 0`
during any sharpening phase."*

At the Lean level we only expose the scalar `őľ_star ‚Č• 0` ; the pointwise
inequality on `|nSn|` is not a formal Lean quantity (it requires the
tracked curvature maximum `s_max(t)` which is a Lagrangian construct
outside the present formalisation scope).  Downstream consumers
(`MaterialMaxPrinciple.of_HstrainHbdry`) combine this scalar witness with
the paper's ¬ß9 argument (classical, not formalised). -/
structure HasStrainLowerBound
    (_őł : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))) where
  /-- The strain lower bound constant `őľ‚čÜ`. -/
  őľ_star : ‚ĄĚ
  /-- Non-negativity of `őľ‚čÜ`. -/
  őľ_star_nonneg : 0 ‚Č§ őľ_star

/-- **(H-strain) zero-datum witness.** The zero solution trivially
satisfies the normal-strain lower bound with `őľ‚čÜ = 0`. -/
def HasStrainLowerBound.of_zero
    (őł : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (_hőł : ‚ąÄ t, őł t = 0) :
    HasStrainLowerBound őł where
  őľ_star := 0
  őľ_star_nonneg := le_refl _

/-- **(H-bdry) ‚ÄĒ Boundary curvature bound on the material segment.**

Paper ¬ß9.6.3, via Proposition 9.10 (relabelled from *theorem* to
*hypothesis* in the 2026-04-22 revision):
*"There exists `őļ‚čÜ = őļ‚čÜ(őł‚āÄ)` such that, for every material Lagrangian
trajectory `y(t) ‚ąą ‚ąāő©(t)` starting in the support of `őł‚āÄ`, the level-set
curvature satisfies `|őļ(y(t), t)| ‚Č§ őļ‚čÜ` uniformly in `t ‚Č• 0`."*

At the Lean level we only expose the scalar `őļ_star ‚Č• 0`; the pointwise
inequality is a Lagrangian construct outside the present formalisation
scope.  Downstream consumers combine this scalar witness with the paper's
¬ß9 argument (classical). -/
structure HasBoundaryCurvatureBound
    (_őł : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))) where
  /-- The boundary curvature bound constant `őļ‚čÜ`. -/
  őļ_star : ‚ĄĚ
  /-- Non-negativity of `őļ‚čÜ`. -/
  őļ_star_nonneg : 0 ‚Č§ őļ_star

/-- **(H-bdry) zero-datum witness.** The zero solution trivially
satisfies the boundary curvature bound with `őļ‚čÜ = 0`. -/
def HasBoundaryCurvatureBound.of_zero
    (őł : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (_hőł : ‚ąÄ t, őł t = 0) :
    HasBoundaryCurvatureBound őł where
  őļ_star := 0
  őļ_star_nonneg := le_refl _

/-- **(H-őĪ) ‚ÄĒ Thermostat ratio upper bound.**

Paper ¬ß9.8, verbatim:
*"There exists `őĪ‚čÜ < 1` (depending only on `őł‚āÄ`) such that `őĪ(t) ‚Č§ őĪ‚čÜ`
for all `t ‚Č• 0` during any sharpening phase of the evolution"*,
where `őĪ(t) := S_source(t) / (4¬∑|nSn(x(t),t)|¬∑V(t))` is the thermostat
ratio defined in ¬ß9.8.2.

At the Lean level we only expose the scalar `őĪ_star < 1`; the pointwise
inequality is a Lagrangian construct outside the present formalisation
scope.  Paper Proposition 9.11 asserts `(H-őĪ) ‚áí (H-strain) + (H-bdry)`;
the Lean version is `HasStrainLowerBound.of_thermostat` +
