/-- **Conditional-regularity alias matching the paper's ¬ß9.6.3 statement.**

`MaterialMaxPrinciple.of_HstrainHbdry` re-exposes the existing
`MaterialMaxPrinciple` constructor pattern under the paper's naming.  The
hypothesis bundles `HasStrainLowerBound` and `HasBoundaryCurvatureBound`
document the conditional context (paper ¬ß9.6.3); the uniform-`ŠłĘ¬Ļ`
witness (`hOnePropagation` + `hOneSummability`) is the classical ¬ß9
output, taken as an auxiliary input rather than derived from the two
hypothesis bundles alone.  The names match the paper so downstream
consumers can cite (H-strain) + (H-bdry) directly. -/
theorem MaterialMaxPrinciple.of_HstrainHbdry
    {őł : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    (_hStrain : HasStrainLowerBound őł)
    (_hBdry : HasBoundaryCurvatureBound őł)
    (hOnePropagation :
      ‚ąÉ M : ‚ĄĚ, ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí hsSeminormSq 1 (őł t) ‚Č§ M)
    (hOneSummability :
      ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
        Summable (fun n : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ =>
          (fracDerivSymbol 1 n) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (őł t) n‚ÄĖ ^ 2)) :
    MaterialMaxPrinciple őł where
  hOnePropagation := hOnePropagation
  hOneSummability := hOneSummability
  freeDerivativeAtKappaMax := True.intro
  materialSegmentExpansion := True.intro
  farFieldBoundary := True.intro

/-- **Conditional-regularity alias under the single-hypothesis (H-őĪ) route.**

Paper Prop 9.11 (`(H-őĪ) ‚áí (H-strain) + (H-bdry) ‚áí Theorem 3`) packaged at
the Lean level: takes `HasThermostatBound` + the classical ¬ß9.8 output
(uniform `ŠłĘ¬Ļ` bound) and returns `MaterialMaxPrinciple`.  The ¬ß9.8
derivation itself (equations 9.8.a through 9.8.g) is not formalised. -/
theorem MaterialMaxPrinciple.of_thermostat
    {őł : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí Lp ‚Ąā 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    (_hAlpha : HasThermostatBound őł)
    (hOnePropagation :
      ‚ąÉ M : ‚ĄĚ, ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí hsSeminormSq 1 (őł t) ‚Č§ M)
    (hOneSummability :
      ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ, 0 ‚Č§ t ‚Üí
        Summable (fun n : Fin 2 ‚Üí ‚Ą§ =>
          (fracDerivSymbol 1 n) ^ 2 * ‚ÄĖmFourierCoeff (őł t) n‚ÄĖ ^ 2)) :
